I've been many times and whether it's a regular night.  restaurant week or $17.70 night in the tavern, it's always a special night when we go to The 1770 House.

Name: 1770 House

Name: 1770 House

Name: 1770 House

Name: 1770 House

Name: 1770 House

Name: Atera
Comments: Great experience. Certainly recommend.

Name: Atera
Comments: OK. I'm not one for superlatives, but I have to say that my dinner at  Atera was the best dining experience one could ever hope for. From the minute you are greeted, until your departure 9 close to three hours later), you are pampered and fed like never before. It was our 25th anniversary, and every staff member knew about it, congratulated us (by name), and made our night feel so extra special. Once one of the amazing staff, David, found out that I was Grateful Dead fan, the music (which was played at the perfect volume) featured a wonderful set of Dead tunes. Now the food: in a word-- beyond. Seventeen courses. Not too stingy, not too much. Actually had to make room for the last two savory courses. (There's always room for dessert-- courses 16 and 17). I did the temperance drink pairing-- crazy inventive and fun (not a must, but if you have a few $ you don't mind spending, it adds a nice comic dimension to an otherwise very serious and very delicious tasting menu. Chef Ronny is on hand (and is very hands on) overseeing every detail.  He is 35, looks like he is 25, and cooks like he's been doing this forever. This is one restaurant experience you cannot miss. As an aside: We stayed over at 11Howard- a beautiful boutique hotel nearby. Had the 6pm Atera seating. Went to AIRE ancient baths after dinner (9-10:30pm)-- around the block-- for an amazing post-dinner spa experience. If you want to be a hero, treat your special someone to a night like this-- it won't be soon forgotten!Extra shout out to David at Atera-- thank you for a very special evening.

Name: Atera
Comments: exceptional meal .  All dishes were superbly presented and perfectly balanced.  I enjoyed all the savory dishes but the last few sweet ones were disappointing.

Name: Atera

As you can imagine this completely ruined my night and I would never imagine that the service staff would speak to their patrons in that manner.  Despite the food, I will recommend to all my family and friends to stay away for the restaurant given my experience.

Name: Atera

Cheers to Chef, for a brilliant execution and the best evening of 2020, yet. Thank you

Name: Atera
Comments: I was rather disappointed with Atera.  The food was fine; it is Michelin star grade.  But the atmosphere was too uptight, the chef looked angry and unhappy and one of the Scot servers was rude.  I am not able to enjoy food in a tense ambiance and for the price I paid I expected the entire staff, starting with the chef, to have minimum charm.  Some dishes were rather heavy:  I wished I had seen more creativity rather than the usual suspects: caviar, uni, foie gras and truffle oil.  I enjoyed the opening cocktail, the dumpling and the passion fruit mochi.  I am a bit concerned by the level of cholesterol that comes as part of the entire tasting menu.  Sadly I will not be coming back, nor will I recommend Atera to others.  Good luck.

Name: Atera
Comments: It is truly a top restaurant and deserve three Michelin stars. Very creative delicious elegant artsy and pleasing menue.

Name: Atera

Name: Atera

Special mention must go to Messrs Abbick and Manka at front of house who genuinely provided some of the best service I‚Äôve ever experienced at any restaurant - the entire team is incredibly friendly and personable.The food was of a very high standard as you‚Äôd expect and immaculately presented. The team were happy to explain more about each dish and their passion for their work was evident. If you have the funds to go (it isn‚Äôt cheap, we saved months for it), enjoy food and you‚Äôre looking for a fine dining experience in NY, I‚Äôd happily recommend this place.

Name: Atera

Just go and be dazzled and oh, get at least one member of your dining party opt for the temperance pairing. Just do it! Xoxo

Name: Atera
Comments: PerfectEach course was impressive

Name: Atera
Comments: As a foodie and a 30-year hospitality professional, this experience was absolutely fascinating!  It felt a little "Eyes Wide Shut" when I first arrived; a very small, intimate dining area (there were only 17 guests for my seating), and the staff was completely silent in front of us to begin.  Service was flawless, and the team moved effortlessly among each other for 15 courses.  A great ballet, and amazing to watch.  The cuisine was creative and flavorful (think Kaluga caviar paired with a quenelle of pistachio gelato and IPA), but I can't honestly think of a single course that I would request again.  This show was all about the ceremony of the service and plate presentation.  I opted for the coursing paired with wine, and I enjoyed several varietals I'd never tried before; Bosco (blended with Vermentino) from Cinque Terre in Northern Italy, Mencia from Ribeira Sacra, Spain.

Name: Atera
Comments: One of the best fine dinning restaurants in NY, had an amazing night there.

Name: Atera
Comments: Atera is exceptional.   The food (about 17 courses!) was amazing.  Very creative, with combinations of food one might never consider yet they all blended beautifully.  The U-shaped table facing the chefs turned out to be a wonderful addition.  All the staff was very attentive, friendly and as interactive as you wanted them to be (or not!).   The service was noteworthy.  Everything you would expect from a Michelin 2 star...and more.   I have never been to a restaurant where so much attention was given to your personal comfort and interests, in addition to proper and timely serving and removal of food and drink.  I would highly, highly recommend Atera.  True, it is expensive, but given the amount and type of food, it was truly worth the money spent, as no expense was spared by the restaurant in the selection, preparation and delivery of the meal.

Comments: We had great food and the service was exceptional.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Everything was done at the highest level. From arrival to departure, everything and everyone was top notch. I highly recommend this as a special occasion restaurant.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Amazing food you get what You pay for. Drinks are a little pricy but overall awesome experience

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: A special birthday treat for dad.  Started off with cocktails and apps in the bar.  Service was a bit slow during happy hour, but it was friendly.  Our server Erin was helpful and friendly in the dining room.  Thank you for making a kid-friendly pasta dish for my 9-year-old.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Service was terrific. Everything prepared to perfection, from hot buttered brioche to dessert. We enjoyed NY strip, mushrooms, baked potato, lobster bisque - all of it outstanding. We were there for a date, but the rest of the dining room on a busy Thursday evening seemed to be exclusively business meetings (which makes sense since the prices will make you look twice if you are not expensing it!) Our server Jeff was knowledgeable about everything from whiskey to the restaurant‚Äôs history. Classic steakhouse with great seafood options as well!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: The caviar with a glass of champagne  was delicious!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: THE ONLY THING THAT KEEPS US FROM GIVING A 5 STAR RATING WAS THE BAR SERVICE.  AFTER WATCHING WAITER WALK BY TO OTHER TABLES FOR 15 MINUTES, I HAD TO ASK HOW TO GET A DRINK.  THE EXCUSE WAS THAT THEY THOUGHT I WAS WAITING FOR SOMEONE WHICH I WAS, BUT I WAS GOING TO WAIT WITH A DRINK WHICH I WAS NEVER OFFERED.  NOT UP TO BARCLAY PRINE STANDARDS.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Engagement - amazing service and food

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Food was amazing. Service was great. This was my second time back and I love it!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Overall, a very nice and unique restaurant. Perfect ambience for a special night out. However, it is very expensive and quite honestly, given the hype and reviews, the food was just average.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Delicious food, wonderful service. Best steak I've ever had.

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: We loved the quiet, calm & comfortable ambiance of the dining room. Our server, Allison was attentive, professional & gave us great recommendations!

Name: Barclay Prime
Comments: Great atmosphere and excellent service but the food was mediocre.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: A great neighborhood restaurant that is predictably amazing!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Wonderful place for Covid 19........so safe.   The patio was so lovely and cozy........feel like in NYC!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Food, service, ambience were all fantastic! Great alfresco dining experience. Service was incredible. Food and wine were out of this world delicious.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: The food was great and the service was fantastic. A lovely candlelit place, great for a date or with a small group.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Amazing food. Definitely will be back

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Such a lovely restaurant. Service is fantastic and food is DELICIOUS! The pasta is amazing!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My waiter Michael was extremely helpful and gave several possibilities since it was my first time in this establishment. I had the scallops for the appetizer, which were amazing and the freshly made ink linguine with lobster with wild mushroom sauce which was complimented by a fine glass of white wine recommended by Michael. He actually brought me options, which I think helped to complete my meal.  It was a wonderful experience!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My daughter has been raving about Barrique for a long time, my first time was amazing!  The food was incredible, the Scallops and Ragu are a must!Friendly staff, great atmosphere, can't wait to go back!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This place redefines Italian Cuisine. Every time I come to LA is one of the places on my list. As a born and raised Italian living in the US for the last 40 years, It takes a ton. to impressed me, but this place, no matter what you are eating, is a notch above the rest.Consistency is another. key to their success. When you come to a place 10 times and it is always great. that says a lot.One not to miss!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Amazing experience.  Great dishes.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: amazing food! Our waiter was informative and attentive.  We highly recommend this lovely, little, taste of Italy!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Fantastic as always!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Barrique was wonderful! It was a quaint, upscale, romantic dinner for two. Service was excellent across every staff member we encountered. The food was delicious and thoughtfully prepared. My favorite dish was the scallop starter. I felt everything was well priced for the quality and experience :]

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: AMAZING wow What a treat this place is the best! Truly!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: What a beautiful experience to be out after being home for months. The food was amazing, the waiter super friendly and the ambiance romantic and wonderful. Highly recommended!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This was the most enjoyable evening!The service was excellent, the food fantastic!We cannot wait to go back and are fortunate to live only 15 min. away!!!!Birte

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Our first time dining out since the Pandemic and it was heaven! Everything was delicious and wonderful! We were very comfortable with the health and safety standards they had implemented. Most of the tables in this restaurant are outside but we set inside with some other diners (since outside was full) and felt very safe.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: A great spot for a delicious meal! the service was great, made us feel like they knew us. will definitely be back.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Always a great meal! We go regularly, and have never been disappointed.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Great food. Great service. Very romantic! I definitely recommend it.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: This meal was beyond amazing!! One of my top five meals in the last five years!! Can‚Äôt wait to go back!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: First dining out in months...  Barrique never disappoints and tonight was not exception.  Happy to see them open and several other couples enjoying the evening.Staff wore masks & gloves and the spacing of tables was appropriate and safe.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Excellent quality, service and ambiance.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Great experience

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: I would put Barrique up there with any Italian in LA, they also have some specialty dishes that are very unique and can't find anywhere else.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: The people were very friendly and very pleasant. I liked the pasta in Al dente very deliciously.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Fillet mignon was on the dry, side.sea-bass was so-so.Nice servers.A bit overpriced.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Excellent service, delicious food, romantic ambiance. Took my boyfriend for his birthday dinner who is a major Italian foodie and he said its his favorite meal/restaurant in LA. Brought our own bottle of wine, for which our waiter researched and then suggested dishes that would pair well with our wine. Will return for any special event.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: We loved the food and ambiance.  The restaurant is charming and homey.  Excellent pastas.  Attentive service.  We will return.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My boyfriend and I come here for both of our birthdays every year and we are never disappointed! From the mouth watering food to our favorite server Michael who is so sweet and always provides the best wine recommendations Barrique is easily our favorite restaurant in Santa Monica.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Delightful place‚Äî-food and service were amazing!  Fantastic wine list!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Best scallops and best filet ever.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Barrique is a hidden gem on main street Venice. The the ambiance is romantic and the food is great. It was very noisy however and the seating is quite close.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: My first time there and our family spends a lot of our time indulging in great meals. Went in for a blow dry today and was told to go to Barrique! Amazing meal, service and warm hospitality. We loved the prosciutto and burrata and beet pasta as an appetizer. The gentle flavor of the pasta was so delicious and did not make you feel heavy.  The prosciutto was perfect and the serving was so generous. I had the special lobster ravioli with black truffle in lobster bisque. It was as amazing as it sounds. I could not stop  till my husband gave me a piece of his rib eye. It was flavored perfectly with the sea salt that reminded me of Hawaiian sea salt (I‚Äôm born and raised on Maui) it was tender and tasted like wagyu. I left giggling and extremely happy. The meal was so incredible we had to call the restaurant to tell them and spoke to Tony who was so receptive and appreciative. Michael was our waiter and made the dining experience perfect. This is a gem of a restaurant! Our son Keanu has gone there and told us about it and now I know why he raves about it! We will be back!!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Truly wonderful dining experience!Food was amazing and the atmosphere relaxing but romantic.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Best appetizers, pasta, filet mignon!  We sat in the bottom floor next to the kitchen and enjoyed the delicious smells wafting throughout our dinner.  Service, ambience, everything was fantastic!

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Very friendly service, perfect dinner experience

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Our dinner was amazingly yummy! Our waiter was super attentive. It was an incredibly enjoyable evening from start to finish.

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: Best Italian restaurant in the area

Name: Barrique Venice
Comments: We absolutely love this wonderful Italian restaurant for a romantic night out together. This was for Valentines and they kept their regular menu which we much preferred. The octopus starter, wild boar ragu pasta, and chocolate desert were all outstanding. And I lived in Italy for 8 years so I can truly say that! Definitely one of the best restaurants in the area.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Order the bone in ribeye, it's the reason you came, it's amazing.Also, oysters are great and you cannot lose with the sides

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Bavette√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s is by far my favorite restaurant.  We split oysters and shrimp which was very good.  Smoked salmon Caesar salad which was fabulous. Oh....-and the warm bread with amazing crust was divine.  Salmon dish slightly spiced was delicious. Loaded baked potato with diced bacon very tasty. Son in law had a steak that was very good and my daughter had chicken.  Everything was delicious.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food lived up to the hype!!! But the plate that stole the show was the Brussel Sprouts!!! Never in my wildest dreams did I expect them to be this good! Highly recommend them!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing steakhouse in Chicago! Great for a date night or birthday dinner! Service was excellent and food was outstanding!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: I had been looking forward to my reservations for months.  It was a late night reservation due to availability.  We ordered an appetizer that was forgotten about until we reminded our server.  It was brought out moments before our entr√É¬©e.  This put a damper on a highly anticipated date night for my husband's birthday.  The appetizer was later comped and service was good up until we had to flag down our server to get our dessert wrapped up to go.  Food was good but the service will not have me returning.  There are far better restaurants with top notch service for the price.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best restaurant in the city consistently top notch

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Everything was great, service, food, ambiance. We had to book our reservation well in advance, but it lived up to the wait. Would recommend, and would go again.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Ambiance and food  were outstanding. Possibly the best steak dinner my wife and I have ever had.  We both had the filet . Cooked to perfection and melted in your mouth. We were celebrating my wife's birthday and I called ahead for reservations and table on the main floor. Great table but our server never mentioned the occasion to my wife. Would highly recommend for outstanding food,  terrific surroundings and memorable night.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Slow service and did not honor reservation time

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best steakhouse in the city. And the seafood is amazing as well.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The filet mignon was cooked to perfection .  The service from Klause was excellent. We highly recommend this romantic and fantastic place.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Best steak in Chicago.  Would definitely recommend to anyone!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: We were sat at a table towards the door last night. Very drafty when the door opened. Disappointing they did not do more to keep the doors from being open at same time.Food was very good. I thought the service was just average. Was expecting exceptional experience, was just pretty good

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Our waiter Ben was great, we didn√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t feel rushed. We sat downstairs in a booth and the music and atmosphere was nice . The bottle of wine we had paired beautifully with our steak .

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The best!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Very enjoyable place to visit, the burger is a must!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: One of the best steaks in Chicago! Try bone marrow and ribeye, they are the must.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Steak had to be sent back twice and on the third time it was overcooked and tasted terrible. Huge disappointment but the waiter was very good and they were nice enough to remove my steak from the bill. Sides and apps were delicious. Very very dark restaurant.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: I try and get to Bavettes as often as possible - amazing place.  Had difficulty with my prior visit as I had an 8:00 PM reservation (Downstairs - Parlor) and they seated me at 9:20 PM so I was very upset.  This reservation would be my last if that happened again but they were perfect in everyway on this visit.  We sat downstairs (preferred space), waiter was awesome and the food is always the star here.  Bavette's has the best atmosphere in the city - we will be back!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Went to celebrate my daughter√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s birthday- the hostess acknowledged that and then no one after that mentioned her birthday. Somewhat of a bummer as several tables near us were served desserts with sparklers.  We were lucky that Erik finally made it back to our table to get a dessert order let alone send sparklers. Laid back is one thing but Erik takes it to an art form. Food was wonderful, back staff was on the ball, Erik seemed not to care

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Very good food, but not exceptional within this price range.  Terrific, friendly and timely service.  Good wine selection at reasonable prices.  Background music is too loud and interferes with conversation.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Waiting for a reservation without knowing how long the table is going to be, being told that it's 2mins which turns into 10mins is frustrating. Multiple times they got the order wrong and I've cooked better $70 Ribeyes at home

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Waited 40 minutes to be sat, and then were sat in the basement

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food was good and service was very friendly but timing of food delivery was uneven. We ordered three steaks, all medium...one came out medium, another medium-well and a third well-done. All top quality beef but not as ordered. Sides large and good. We had a booth, which was great.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The food was great and we enjoyed the atmosphere and music!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Food was excellent service and waiting time was right on schedule . Staff did a great job

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Took me several months to get a reservation but it was worth it. My wife and I went with my brother and his wife. For appetizers we ordered the steak tartare, shrimp cocktail and half dozen oysters. All were great. For steaks the bone in ribeye and the petite fillet. They were cooked perfectly with great flavor. For sides, the sweet potatoes, crab stuffed avocado salad, truffle mac and cheese and elote style corn. For me the elote style corn was the best but all were good. As for the wine, I highly recommend the Colombo Apertura Pinot Noir. One of the best wines I have had in a long time. No dessert unfortunately but if you see the amount of food we ordered you will understand why we passed.The ambiance of the place was also very cool. The music was great and the noise level was a little high but sitting in the booth we didn't have much difficulty hearing. There is a great bar area both upstairs and down. Only complaint is the restroom situation. They are single restrooms and there was at least one to two waiting in line. Not a big deal.Overall an excellent meal and great scene. Would love to go back so I better get to work trying to secure another reservation. People did walk in without a reservation and I overheard them being told hour thirty to an hour forty-five. Not that unusual for a high-end restaurant downtown but I prefer a reservation.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing food and great service.  Definitely worth a trip to Bavette if you are going through Chicago.  YUM!!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: It was fabulous !!!! We love Bavettes ...It is our most favorite restaurant ever !!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Well executed food but the service left quite a bit to be desired.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing service and food was outstanding.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Went to Bavette's for a date night and the food was really good! Only disappointment was the length of time we were there. We ended up being there for 3.5 hours due to the wait time on our steaks. Also, I ordered a bone-in filet cooked medium+ and it was pretty well-done except close to the bone. Still very flavorful though!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: We were there for my boyfriends surprise 30th! The staff went above and beyond to make this special surprise perfect!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: The first time I came to Bavette's we only had appetizers and side dishes--and it was amazing. I wanted to come back and get to experience one of the best steaks in Chicago. It definitely lived up to the hype and as always, the sides (specifically the wedge salad with their famous bacon and the garlic mashed potatoes) were fantastic as well. The ambiance makes you feel like you've stepped into a classic Chicago speakeasy, especially in the basement and the service was on point. Great spot to celebrate a special occasion.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Bavettes came highly recommended. First of all, it is quite dark in the dining room. The rest rooms are old and small. The bar area has a rather nice ambiance. There is an additional dining room in the "dungeon" which provides less noise and more privacy. The food is pricey and I would suffice it to say that you do not necessarily get your money's worth. The portions are relatively small. The filet mignon and lamb chops were average. However, the crab was excellent! The service is attentive. I think there are many other superior options for steaks, chops and seafood in the area.  We will not be returning to Bavettes anytime soon.

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Loved the food! Came out very fast. Service was amazing. Food was hot and seasoned just right. Will be back!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: So good! Their Mac and cheese with bacon √∞≈∏¬§¬§

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Amazing! Great experience!

Name: Bavette's
Comments: Wonderful anniversary dinner.  Impeccable service. Phenomenal food.  My favorite restaurant in Chicago,

Name: Bavette's
Comments: My wife and I had an excellent time.  The ambiance was amazing!  The music playing was sultry and seductive.  The food was great!!!! The service was outstanding!!!! I would recommend this restaurant to anyone!!! Perfect date night restaurant!!!

Name: Benu
Comments: Splendid, best quail I have ever had. The caviar with egg is extremely tasty.

Name: Benu
Comments: Wonderful evening of fine dining.

Name: Benu
Comments: We have been wanting to try Benu for years, so were excited to finally make a night of dining here.  The service was outstanding.  The timing of the dishes coming out was excellent and we found the servers to be professional and also very charming.  The food, though, fell a bit short of expectations for a 3-star restaurant.  Most of the starting tastes were delicious, but some of the main courses were not very good.  The xiao long bao and beef courses were excellent, but the soup was rather bland and the BBQ quail had an overwhelming smoke flavor that was unappealing.  After dining at Quince, Acquerello, and Manresa, we were disappointed in the food at Benu.  It was a good experience overall, but not really worth the price in comparison with similar class restaurants.

Name: Benu
Comments: Technicality wise it is at the highest caliber. Service was impeccable. Atmosphere is very calm and intricate. Personally, it felt amazing to see simple everyday Asian food presented in exquisite ways.Lots of praise for the Benu team

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing from start to finish. The food, service and hospitality were unmatched.

Name: Benu
Comments: Loved every dish and service was superb

Name: Benu
Comments: Really great food. Some courses were out of this world, some courses were just really good but not worth the cost. All in all a great experience for a special occasion.

Name: Benu
Comments: One of The most amazing meals of my life. The food was perfect. And THE SERVICE: like a ballet! Also The Ambience, The Music. The beautiful Wine list! A Trip to San Francisco is only complete it if you visit Benu: The Food Cathedral!

Name: Benu
Comments: The food was exceptional

Name: Benu
Comments: The xiao long bao is an explosion of flavor - a truly amazing creation!  This alone made this a life experience.  Flawless!

Name: Benu
Comments: Food is good, no problemNeed a more comfortable chair to be honest.And need to increase the distance between tables defintely.

Name: Benu
Comments: Innovative and classic at the same time. What an experience!

Name: Benu
Comments: Absolutely excellent and attentive service of 3 Michelin star.   The food was wonderful.   Thank you

Name: Benu
Comments: it has actually improved from last time I was there, thought there was no room to move further, but I am wrong, they can do even better than better

Name: Benu
Comments: Every item of food was truly unique.  The explanation by the staff was very clear and welcome

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing. We‚Äôll be back!

Name: Benu
Comments: I‚Äôm still blown away by the culinary experience and Service. That the Benu team provides. The menu was beyond delightful. Loved the Asian influence and all the delicacies. Pictures speak for itself.

Name: Benu
Comments: Anniversary dinner!

Name: Benu
Comments: We went for our anniversary. Very beautiful dishes and tasty as well. I don‚Äôt like raw food so Benu is the right type of restaurant for me. Most of dishes are from China and Korea. If you like Asian food or want to try Asian food, then you will like it

Name: Benu
Comments: Worth it. It's a month of daycare/preschool for one kiddo. But I like good food/booze, so does my husband, and I appreciated the multicultural, equal gender reppin that night.

Name: Benu
Comments: Most incredible restaurant on the West Coast, worth every penny and the entire trip!

Name: Benu
Comments: Outstanding quality of food, drinks, presentation, and service.

Name: Benu
Comments: An upscale dining experience great for a date night.  The food and service were excellent, but be prepared to spend some serious money.

Name: Benu
Comments: Each dish looked like a masterpiece. The taste  of the food divine. The minimalist decor soothes the senses and awakens imagination. Excellent service.

Name: Benu
Comments: Repeat visit to this exceptional restaurant. Interesting dishes, wonderful presentation, excellent wine pairing. Overall, an extraordinary experience.

Name: Benu
Comments: A new found appreciation for ingredients I grew up with. A fascinating and well thought out twist on Korean and Chinese cuisine. One of the most perfect meals I‚Äôve had. Every bite was a dream and the portions were perfect. Benu is an institution and a must visit if you‚Äôre in SF!

Name: Benu
Comments: My favourite dining experience to date. We went for our anniversary and the service was beyond impeccable. The flavours were inventive and yet still so delicious. Such a special dining experience!

Name: Benu
Comments: Each dish, brought one by one to the table at a comfortable rate, was amazing.  It felt like we were dining in our own home as there was continual interaction with the kindly, professional wait staff.  They were eager to answer questions and seemed to enjoy how much we were enjoying the experience.  I loved the presentation of each delicacy in a special bowl or on a plate made just for that offering.  The only flaw to our evening, one which was not under the control of the waitstaff was the loud talking from a nearby table of business people who could not have actually been eating, or at least not really savoring what was being brought to them.  The food itself was totally worth the price, which is admittedly not for the faint of heart.  You cannot get these dishes anywhere else and the ingredients are rare or difficult to source. The wine offerings were similarly stunning and so were the prices for wines by the glass, which added substantially to our final bill.  It was a special event for us, so we didn't mind the loud conversation nearby us nor the final bill-- we were prepared for that .  It was an epic evening.

Name: Benu
Comments: It‚Äôs really an amazing restaurant which deserved 3 stars Michelin

Name: Benu
Comments: Hands down the very best service you will ever receive, and the food was euphoric.

Name: Benu
Comments: Really enjoyed the meal.   Loved the Asian influences.

Name: Benu
Comments: have good service

Name: Benu
Comments: I have twice dined at Benu!! The cuisine and the staff are quite amazing! Also, I really appreciated that the tasting menu had quite a few new additions between my 1st visit and most recent visit!

Name: Benu
Comments: Great Meal as the last time. Great food and service from start to the desserts. Every time will be back to SF will visit Benu. All best for all team great job.

Name: Benu
Comments: Sublime restaurant experience.

Name: Benu
Comments: Delicious. Innovative flavor profiles, consistent and excellent execution, thoughtful and perfectly balanced wine pairingsThe service was knowledgeable, professionally enthusiastic, and unobtrusive. Loved our main wait person and the somm was excellent!

Name: Benu
Comments: Outstanding ! Never disappointed! The food is exquisite, innovative, yet with a respect to the spirit of traditional Chinese and Asian gastronomy. The staff is A+.

Name: Benu
Comments: Creative and delicious food in a wonderfully sedate setting.

Name: Benu
Comments: Pretentious & largely tasteless food served by smug, arrogant staff.

Name: Benu
Comments: Amazing place to have one of the best nights of your life! Special Mention to the wine pairing, it was simply perfect for the tasting menu, which is an artwork from Corey. My most sincerely congratulations for him! Every course was a tremendous experience of flavors and textures in another different level. Also the service was spectacular. Every person knows what they are talking about and they make you feel really nice during the whole experience. Really really happy for being there.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Where does one begin. My God, this place was top drawer all the way. Our server Mathew was incredible,  he asked,  he explained, he was attentive,  on a Saturday night no less w all the craziness that ensues on a busy night.  The food was off the charts,  the stuffed peppers and the Saffron crepe where just intense. The cocktails were beautifully orchestrated,  overall a great time and will certainly be returning when I get back to Raleigh.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Favorite restaurant in Raleigh, hands down. Really special new things to try, along with wonderful versions of classics. Seriously, incredible flavors, amazing atmosphere and design - love.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: My second time here and was pleased to bring along three others that had not been to Bida Manda before. It was the perfect experience. From the unique cocktails, amazing apps, tasty entrees and superior service.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food was great!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: I was thrilled to finally be able to visit Bida Manda!  Due to its deserved popularity, short notice evening reservations are hard to come by, so lunch proved to be a great option.  I thoroughly enjoyed the pork belly soup.  It is unlike anything I've ever had.  For a soup, it is incredibly rich and filling.  The portion was so large that I had more than enough for lunch the next day.  Our server Sophia was so friendly and knowledgeable.  The only downside (and a small one for me) is that the table next to us was very very close.  I look forward to going back to Bida Manda and trying some of the other great menu options!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The food was delicious! I'll definitely be coming back!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Amazing meal. The most flavorful dishes I have had. I recommend the papaya salad with duck.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The Green Papaya salad with Lemongrass Chicken is absolutely delightful. Highly recommended.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We attended dinner at Bida Manda for our second anniversary. The staff was very friendly and the food was very good. They start by bringing out some complimentary shrimp chips, which were really pleasant. Our waiter recommended the lettuce wraps as an appetizer and they were hands down the best dish of the night... I‚Äôm not usually a lettuce wrap kind of guy either. We split the Manda Herb Salad with chicken and Tom Khem (short ribs and pork belly) and they balanced each other nicely. The short ribs were a little dry, but the gravy and fatty pork belly balanced them out well and they tasted delicious. The salad was really nicely balanced. The food is about $20 per entree, but we have enough leftovers for both of our lunches tomorrow, so the value is good for the price.After the waiter packed up our food, he brought us some complimentary macarons to celebrate our anniversary. They were the best macarons we‚Äôve ever had, and I‚Äôve been to Paris. To cleanse our palates at the end of the meal, they served us each a small shot of lemon juice, lime juice, and ginger, which was a great way to wrap up the wonderful experience. We‚Äôre moving soon, but if we‚Äôre ever in town again, we‚Äôll be revisiting Bida Manda for sure.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Our server Savannah was fantastic, so was the food and drink. Always a great time!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Really delicious and great service.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Food took over an hour to come out. I had ordered a thai tea and it was not ready. They said it would be ready in 5-10 minutes. 20 minutes later they brought out a tea that was nothing like how it normally is. When the food came out it came out very spread out. over 15 minutes between when my food came out and when my guests did. I was very disappointed by this since I have had good experiences in the past and wanted to share with others but was very much let down.  Food was good unsure if I would bring friends for lunch session again.

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Service was super; but too noisy, otherwise great!

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Great place, great foodHad a great date time with hubby

Name: Bida Manda Restaurant and Bar

Name: Caf√© Monarch
Comments: From the very first minute we walked in the door, we felt welcomed & that they were happy we had come! The most beautiful restaurant we have ever dined in! Our hostess was lovely & so sweet. This is our 3rd visit to Cafe Monarch & we see something new each time. There is so much beauty everywhere, we just try to soak it all in. Gorgeous fresh white roses & greenery centerpiece, plus a real flame lamp. Beautiful lamp stands all over with real lighted candles on them. Chandeliers are amazing, so sparkling & spectacular! Service is perfect in every way, such attention to detail & so gracious, makes you feel like some kind of royalty! We  were blessed with Kyle as our waiter, who instantly remembered us from the month before, when we celebrated my birthday. This time we brought our daughter for her 50th birthday & she was overwhelmed. Just delightful in every way! Spectacular food, every course, every bite, phenomenal. You really just can't believe how wonderful it all is! Best food we have ever had, in any restaurant, anywhere! No exaggeration. When our daughter got up to use the restroom, a waiter refolded her napkin, so when she came back it was just like new. A nice touch! Attention to every detail imaginable! I love the detailed description of each course, by our server when they brought our food. For her birthday, they brought out the most amazing chocolate dessert, remembering that she was gluten free. It came with a lighted sparkler in it, so fun & a great picture moment! The cocktails were pretty & so delicious! Kyle was outstanding throughout! He remembered so many things about my tastes in food & made accommodations accordingly. Very impressive!! We plan to dine at Cafe Monarch as often as possible, making sure we bring all of our family, at one time or another. Our daughter is already planning to come back for their 30th wedding anniversary in December & they live in Colorado! That's how great Cafe Monarch is! We absolutely LOVE it! Thanks Kyle! So Special

Name: Caf√© Monarch
Comments: This is, non-stop, our favorite restaurant in the PHX area, and it is special enuf for the most special occasion.  We hosted our friend for dinner, and tho she's lived here for over 25 years, this was her first time at Monarch.  It was a truly wonderful evening!  As always, the wait staff (Noah helped us out on this occasion) is knowledgable, attentive and truly seems to enjoy every part of the job at Monarch.  Having been closed due to Covid for 2 months, Noah was ecstatic to be back at work!  The food choices, and willingness of the kitchen to adapt to individual tastes and needs, are marvelous.  We all had the cauliflower soup, which is my perennial favorite 1st course here.  Two of us had the soft-shell crab and our friend had the compressed watermelon salad as the 2nd course, and we all enjoyed every bite.  I had the rib eye and stuffed zucchini blossom next and they had the lobster raviolo and we were all happy.  My entree was the Ahi; they had the seafood with gnocchi and we all agreed we had made excellent choices.  We have learned over time that doing the wine pairings not only provides us with a wonderful opportunity to try new wines, but with the wait staff all being sommeliers, it adds to the evenings drama and pleasure.  Due to our birthday celebration, they treated us to a tasting platter of 3 marvelous desserts - what a sweet, sweet ending to a perfect evening.

Comments: Chez Billy SudMy wife and I eloped earlier in the day and came to Chez Billy Sud to celebrate our first meal together. We wanted a good outdoor dinner, given the COVID-19 environment. We received a round of champagne on the house, plus an additional round from another family kind enough to surprise us with one.And when we left, everyone at the restaurant started clapping for us. It was a special moment that will stick with us for our lifetime.Overall 5 Star experience - no question. We‚Äôll be back!

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: Chez Billy Sud is a true neighborhood restaurant that works well for either a casual night out or a more special date night. The food is always on point and the execution is true to the classics. Nothing is 're-imagined' or 'interpreted', just technically cooked extremely well. Our server (whose name I didn't catch, regretfully) was tremendous and seemed to be handling 1/2 the dining room incredibly graciously. We had drinks at 3 different restaurants during our night, and the ones at Chez billy Sud were the most consistently executed and well-balanced. Consistency is a sadly overlooked attribute when everyone wants to be 'new' but Chez Billy Sud continues to exemplify the idea that care and execution are the real drivers of success. We'll absolutely be back, especially for the patio and rose in the summer / spring.

Name: Chez Billy Sud
Comments: This is an 'casual' vibe but upscale French restaurant, elegant, charming, with impeccable service.  The food is outstanding.  Highly recommended.

Maybe simplicity is better for them, but we thought it was a bit inhospitable. He said there were so many coffee places nearby... Not a big problem.  Overall, it was a very nice lunch.

The sweet, light-filled and calm ambiance of the restaurant is a welcome respite in trying times, and we'll definitely go back.

At that point the wine bottle was finished and I had finished my meal so we decided to not complain further but pay the bill and go home.

The staff is a bit fussy so good luck trying to get something redone.

Top class food for sure, at same time cozy and casual atmosphere, I wish they make a little more reasonable prices. Like, 36 oz bone-in ribeye steak was $205 that perfect size to share for 2, $102.50 each person, probably $20-$30 higher than Mastro‚Äôs, BOA, etc.

Comments: My experience here was amazing. Great food & impeccable service. We had many things on the menu & they were all exquisitely done. For meats, the Porcini rubbed short ribs are fantastic. If you can afford it, the 36oz Ribeye (or NY Steak) is a must for the table. It was dry aged spectacularly. Truly one of the best steaks in all of LA.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: I don‚Äôt know where to start. I arrived and several of my guests preceded me. Their wine has been decanted but no water poured as they waited. After about 5 minutes the waitress appeared and I told her that we would start with champagne, foccacia and salad immediately but she responded that we had to order everything at the same time or the chef wouldn‚Äôt even look at the order. So we sat and decided the entire order which I then shared with waitress. I ordered lots of food and then asked if we could order more just in case we wanted more afterwards and was told that it depended on whether or not they needed to turn the table. The sides came out first and after a few minutes we served them and them finally ate them before the meet arrived. I brought the service issue to my servers attention and she then proceeded to avoid me even though I had told her earlier that i was picking up the tab for our party of 6. Empty water glasses and plates left on the table between courses. I flagged down other servers or personnel to get service. It was a rather  unfortunate series of events that made for a less than special evening for the birthday celebration intended.

Comments: Our sixth visit was unfortunately our least favorite. We LOVE Chi Spacca. Even this off night was pretty wonderful. That said, we noticed a pricing issue between what was on the menu and what we were charged for an item, and one of our meat dishes was far too rare for us to enjoy, which was especially disappointing since we had ordered the same thing three times before, and it was fantastic. Service is always terrific, and if this had been my first visit, I probably would have loved it, but since we have seen Chi Spacca at its most spectacular, this visit was a bit of a letdown.

Name: chi SPACCA
Comments: Most of our food was outstanding. The oil-soaked bread with burrata, the little gem salad, the plate of citrus (a wonderfully refreshing palate cleanser before the main course), the broccoli, and the lemon posset with balsamic were all delightful. The only dish that my made my partner and I look at each other and say anything other than, "Wow, this is perfect," was, surprisingly enough, the meat entree. We ordered the Porcini Rubbed Beef Short Ribs, and I have to say that the salsa verde was more enjoyable than the meat itself. They tasted overcooked and were somewhat lacking in flavor. That being said, we still cleaned the plate as the short ribs would still blow most out of the water - even if they didn't live up to the chi Spacca standard. Our service didn't meet the typical standard of a award-winning restaurant, either. Our server was not very attentive and we had empty, dirty plates stacked in front us more than once, though I suppose this is better than an over-attentive server, and it may be because we chose counter seating rather than a table. All in all, I would recommend chi Spacca with an 8/10 stars.

Comments: I really wanted to like this place. While the food was about what was expected, the entire experience was a huge let down. First, we were seated 45 minutes after our reservation, and then it took another 30 just to get service. The restaurant has about 5 tables total, so the fact we RARELY saw our waiter the entire TWO HOURS it took to eat was also extremely unfortunate. The courses came out 30 minutes apart, which was very strange to have a bowl of mashed potatoes sit there for half an hour until the first meat came out. Our waters were never filled, and I think I only got one beer the entire meal because our waiter literally never came back after we ordered our food. Except one time to apologize for how long everything was taking. I will say they gave us complimentary sorbet at the end, probably because it was now 11PM and we were just eating. While the food is tasty, I really don't believe the restaurant is as fine as it seems to have convinced itself it is. For how much it costs, I would definitely go for a more exemplary dining experience elsewhere ie: Bavel.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Exquisite is the best way to describe  the food, service, and ambiance.  From the moment you enter you are made to feel as though you are their only guest. We tried the 7 course tasting menu with the wine pairing and it's obvious that Daniel has everything perfected. The tastes my tongue experienced were out of this world. I can say every dish exceeded my expectations.  The bison and mushroom aperitifs were my personal favorite and I'm usually not a fan of mushrooms.  They even provided personal touches that made it a night we'll never forget.  The staff were so attentive and not in any way rushing you.  I cannot wait to return and of course I highly recommend Daniel to all.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Celebrating an anniversary

Name: Daniel
Comments: Wonderful service and amazing food at Daniel. Made a special night even more special.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Perfection

Name: Daniel
Comments: Do you really need a review for what is arguably the best restaurant in NYC?  It is not inexpensive, but really, if you're reading this, you knew that already.  Service, impeccable.  Food, outstanding.  No better place for a special occasion.   Bonus, Chef Boulud was in the dining room.  I don't know, maybe he's there all the time, but it was cool to see.

Name: Daniel
Comments: This was our third year going to Daniel for our birthday dinner. My daughters share the same birthday, three years apart and I follow a couple of weeks after so we have made it a tradition to go to New York to celebrate. Our first time at Daniel was so amazing we decided it would be our yearly tradition and it has never disappointed. Not only is each plate beautiful and delicious the service and ambiance simply cannot be matched!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Food and service excellent as always. They even made a special dessert when I found I couldn‚Äôt eat what was offered.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Amazing as always!!!  Thank to Elvir for the kitchen tour and chef Will!  Amazing food and service!

Name: Daniel
Comments: My wife and I loved the experience it was superb in every level.I want to give props to the manager Kareem who made sure everything was perfect thru our evening and took us to the kitchen for a photo up.We will definitely be back.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Daniel is amazing! Unforgettable dinner.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Best restaurant in Manhattan,  just amazing food. The service and ambiance are reminiscent of the best Parisian places.

Name: Daniel
Comments: The service was remarkable and outstanding.  The hosts, the sommelier, and the servers went over and beyond to ensure our comfort. We had the four course tasting.  The dessert course was amazing and kept getting better with each offering.  However, the other three courses were very disappointing.  the presentation was good but the taste was not what we expected from a restaurant of this caliber.  It was not pleasing to our palate. Considering the price we pay at this restaurant, we were expecting a lot more in terms of taste.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Incredible tastes and service. They handled dietary restrictions with ease. Very special place

Name: Daniel
Comments: Without a doubt one of the most outstanding meals of our lives. The finest combination of cuisine, service, and ambiance in the United States, if not the world. We were awed by the tasting dinner. Every staff member was superb. Special appreciation to our sommelier who recommended a wonderful wine that was also a good value. We‚Äôll always remember this great evening at Restaurant Daniel.

Name: Daniel
Comments: First visit to this legendary restaurant and it totally lived up to it‚Äôs reputation.Will return.

Name: Daniel
Comments: a fabulous dining experience. Outstanding Menu , great Presentation and first rate service.A true memorable culinary experience!!!

Name: Daniel
Comments: The experience at Daniel was absolutely AMAZING. Everyone was very kind and thoughtful for our special day. The Chef even sent us a customized "Congratulations" desert made with white chocolate and exotic fruits - we very much appreciated this attention. As well as the fresh and warm Madeleines, a delicious french Canelet and mini home-made chocolates using the finest chocolates from all over world. And Thank you again for the very pretty customized menus printed in grand elegance for us. Daniel restaurant  is a true highlight for people who want to experience something which is truly special and unique. We will come back soon. Merci infiniment.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Thank goodness there is still an exceptional dining experience around. I‚Äôd almost given up on dining out. Every place was the same uninspiring Upscale gastro pub trying to put a new spin on old recipes. So many places didn‚Äôt live up to the hype. Daniel is the definition of fine elegant dining. Every bite was creative and perfectly balanced- a foodie‚Äôs dream. Checks all the boxes of what I look for when seeking a new exciting experience. 1. He created things I would never imagine- familiar flavors blended into something new and sensational.2. I could never create this in my house.3. Creates a whole world and experience. For three hours I was removed from time and space and enjoyed one Devine culinary sensory sensation after another of taste smells and textures.Hit every note perfectly like a symphony- the room decor, the lighting, the service, the timing, the wine,  and of course the food.If you are a true foodie ( in search of the next great bit- no matter where - fine dining to food cart) then you must experience Daniel and if you miss and are in search of a whole true fine dining experience put Daniel somewhere top of your list.

Name: Daniel
Comments: 30th wedding anniversary meal went 5 years previous and did not disappoint nothing‚Äôs cheap in New York really so well worth a visit for a special occasion with a quality taste experience and very attentive staff

Name: Daniel
Comments: Very classic and nice setting. Was lucky to see the chef and have a picture with him.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Valentine‚Äôs Day; the special menu was astronomically priced even in relation to other fine-dining NYC tasting menus

Name: Daniel
Comments: Absolutely amazing. Better than Le Bernardin.

Name: Daniel
Comments: One of five must go spots in Manhattan for special occasions. Very pricey but you get what you pay for. Our Valentines Saturday lunch was superb with unmatched seating due to the earlier time. From the reception to departure the highly trained staff makes you welcome with knowledge and lack of pretense. All the four courses were elegant to behold and a symphony of flavors. The dessert course is a profusion of riches crafted under the supervision is the Pastry chef Ghaya Olivera and is equal to the best in the world. Drinks are special with a stellar and expensive list of curated wines. Very highly recommended for anyone‚Äôs bucket list. Bravo!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Dinner at Valentine‚Äôs Day.The food was great as always. Price was double due to Valentine‚Äôs Day. Table was close to the entrance door. Rush service. Unfortunately, I felt it was a sloppy night.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Great time with another couple for V day ,

Name: Daniel
Comments: Elvir is awesome!!!

Name: Daniel
Comments: It was wonderful!

Name: Daniel
Comments: This was one of our favorite dinners Ever!! The service was impeccable. The food was extraordinary. The wine was spectacular!! We will continue to eat at Daniel every time we make it to NYC!! Thank you Daniel for an exceptional dining experience!

Name: Daniel
Comments: Fantastic restaurant in Classic Style. Appropriate interior design. Great service. Amazing food.Overall excellent experience.

Name: Daniel
Comments: Love Daniel been there few time always excellent on every way!!!

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto
Comments: We were adventurous & selected the chef‚Äôs table 8 courses with wine. Totally fabulous! We had such a wonderful evening with friends that was fill with conversation & good food. The pasta was so light light & delicious I‚Äôm envious of the still of those tiny cheese or potato filled delights. My husband loved the flavorful soup course. Best part I stayed on my diet & still lost weight! Gave me new meaning to portion control! It‚Äôs so relaxing to be be not rushed to next course to turn over the table. Can‚Äôt wait to go back!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Outstanding meal and service is perfect.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Visited from California for our 10 year wedding anniversary. They sat us late for our reservation. Took a long time to get served wine. Somal√≠es was unfriendly, uptight, and not helpful. She accidentally poured my husband a glass of red that he did not order spilling it in the process then when she realized she accidentally poured it she made a big scene of taking it off the table. When I asked her what she did with the glass of wine she said it‚Äôs a wash it‚Äôs just sitting in the back. For the price of the meal you would think she would just leave the glass for my husband to enjoy.  The restaurant is beautiful looks like a movie set but the meal and service was not worth the price of a fine dining experience.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Visited with my college daughter and teen son on a visit to NYC. It was the highlight meal of our trip, as in the past.Love everything about this amazing restaurant!

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Mind blowing food experience

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Inventive but excellent food, soothing surroundings, and top-notch service!

Name: Del Posto

Can‚Äôt wait to go back. You‚Äôre gonna pay when doing the wine pairing but it‚Äôs soooo worth it. You only live once.

Name: Del Posto

Comments: I took my husband to DelPosto for his 56th birthday after seeing it being mentioned in a Daily News article as one of the best Italian restaurants and confirmation of same by a good friend. Great for date night, birthdays and Valentine‚Äôs Day! We had the 5 course tasting menu.  Every dish was excellent even though our favorites were the linguine with geoduck, the shellfish stew, the branzino and the antipasti with sweet potatoes and pears!!!!  All delicious! The warm bread stick with the clotted cream and olive oil was addicting!  The whole team made our experience memorable especially Damiano and Jaziel! They didn‚Äôt miss a beat!! They even gave me a small foot stool to rest my handbag on so it wouldn‚Äôt be on the floor!!! Who does that???  We will definitely go back again!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Del Posto is one of the most elegant restaurants I‚Äôve ever been to. We did the Captains Menu where you tell the waiter your preferences and he selects the 8 courses. Every course was delicious. It was definitely pricey but well worth it for a special occasion.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: This is my all time favorite restaurant in the world.  I make sure when I travel to NYC that this place is on my dinner list.  That is a lot to say coming from an Irish guy from Chicago üòâ

Name: Del Posto
Comments: This is one of the best restaurants around.  Quality of food and service is top notch.  You‚Äôre going to pay for it, but you won‚Äôt forget it.

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto

Lol.  The largest portion on the menu was the butter.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Outstanding service. A very enjoyable last evening in New York.

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Family of 4 wearing jeans and sneakers seated in main dining room for New Years Eve Lunch. Name: Del Posto
Comments: Excellent service dining experience combined with an amazing meal and wine pairing experience We did 5 course tasting menu

Name: Del Posto
Comments: It was wonderful and one of the best meals ever!!

Name: Del Posto
Comments: The host should of been more welcoming. I had to interrupt them so we can be acknowledged. Everything after that was amazing. I will give them a second chance.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Mike was a great host and server etc.

Name: Del Posto
Comments: My boyfriend and I had a fantastic experience dining at Del posto.I would definitely recommend this restaurant to my friends and family

Name: Del Posto

Name: Del Posto
Comments: Food was superb! Service was excellent! It was a bitter cold grey day that was warmed and brightened by the caring attention we received. We look forward to our next visit.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Perfect in every way!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Wow! My guest(s) and I couldn‚Äôt get enough of the Chef‚Äôs tasting menu until we were full. Definitely a special occasion/date night experience to be remembered.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Exquisite sushi, robatayaki and other Japanese dishes, well plated with friendly but not obtrusive service. Would be very happy to return once it is safe to eat out again!

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: I went to Double Knot with some colleagues and we not only found the food superb, but the service and ambiance were delightful as well. Great for girls night out, larger groups or sexy time with that special someone. Great vibe overall.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Unfortunately, I found the food bland.  And while the ambiance and drinks were good, it wasn't worth the money.  I will not go back.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This is our second time visiting and we love the atmosphere and the food.  Everything was great.  The service was outstanding and the food was delicious.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: It wasn‚Äôt clear that the bar reservation wasn‚Äôt eligible for happy hour specials

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This place is top 5 in Philly easy.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Our second visit. really love everything about it. all the small plates so interesting. Evening menu has nine sections!  Incredible variety and assortment can be a bit overwhelming! First visit we did the tasting menu but this time we felt confident enough to order a la carte. Unfair to call it a sushi restaurant since it is much more than that. You may wish to peruse the menu online before you go. In the cold section we loved hamachi and avocado salad. I was not a fan of the king oyster mushroom but partner liked it. It's too rubbery for my taste.On the  "crispy" menu, the wings were wonderful. next time I'd like to try the Japanese fried chicken. We had the beef dumpling in broth that was delicious. My menu said beef soup dumplings which they are not. Partner's menu just said the correct "beef dumpling." Crab udon delish but not much crab. My favorite offerings at the restaurant are the Robotayaki especially the ribeye and Kobe beef. You may want to order double and triple of those. The lobster claw was also great. No room for dessert. Schulson does a great job with decor and fun experiences which enhance the whole experience and also manages to hire staff that are really friendly, professional and knowledgeable. They seem to be having fun even tho they are working.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Dinning at Double Knot was definitely an experience. We had a reservation and ate at the counter downstairs. We had the chef‚Äôs tasting menu and they accommodated my shellfish allergy and it being lent. My one complaint is that we felt rushed and like we needed to eat as fast as possible. At one point we had four plates arrive at the same time.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: The upstairs bar area where you wait smelled horrible.  A mixture of bleach and feet.  Nearly left while waiting.  It‚Äôs not a good way to start and end the evening Food and service downstairs was excellent.  Sad that the experience was tainted

Name: Double Knot
Comments: This was our 3rd time coming to double knot and we enjoyed it just as the last one. I had the lovers knot cocktail which was amazing. Me and boyfriend ordered the Japanese fried chicken as something new to try. Flavour explosion in our mouths. It was the best thing ever.  Our waitress was Caydie and she was a sweetheart. Very informative on the items on the table and attentive to us.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Service was excellent! Food was excellent except Brussels sprouts had too much balsamic vinegar.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: While the food was good, as always, this time we had a new server/bartender who didn't understand that soy is in all soy sauce. In fact, she argued with me about it until one of her colleagues that explained to her, very patiently, that soy, by the very nature of the thing, is made of fermented soybeans, and is not related to its gluten content. With my soy allergy, this is rather an important point. Still, she meant well, and other than this, we had a good time there.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Omakase chef's tasting was delicious.  Server and female manager were rushing our table, clearing plates before we were done; the manager even took away my empty water glass after dessert without bringing it back (or refilling it). It was so obvious that they wanted to flip the table.  Unprofessional and not appreciated; our party of 3 spent $400 on dinner.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: best sushi place in town considering location ambiance and food!

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: I forget our waiters name but he made the night with his wine and food recommendations.

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Excellent, as always! It‚Äôs on our rotation for business and pleasure!

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: On the pricey side but some of the best sushi I‚Äôve had in quite some time.

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

The tapas menu allowed us to try many different menu items and everything was great!

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Awesome dinner! We did the Chef‚Äôs Tasting menu and each course was better than the last. Cocktails were great, food was amazing, service was top notch.

Name: Double Knot

I must recommend: octopus sushi, duck scrapple, any robitiaki item, and their mochi ice cream. Overall, it was a great experience for a special occasion

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Always enjoy our time at Double Knot! Service is top-notch, the downstairs area is great for a date night, and the food is spectacular. We did the tasting menu and chose our selections. Everything was delicious and it let us try things we wouldn‚Äôt normally order. Food came promptly as it was ready, and, as fast eaters, we appreciated the pace. I believe the portions were smaller with the tasting menu but we did not leave hungry. We sat at the bar and the bartender was super helpful and patient as we made our decisions. One male bartender was a bit loud and I heard him complaining a bit, but other than that, we very much enjoyed the whole experience. Definitely a place for a special occasion or to take visitors!

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: It was good! Pricy but good!

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot
Comments: Always a great overall experience

Name: Double Knot

Name: Double Knot

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: It was great to finally experience this sister restaurant to MB Post, which is just next door. As the name suggests, the cuisine is seafood oriented, which was fresh and delicious with influences from around the world and domestically.  We ate the grilled octopus, soft shell crab, and lobstah roll.  All were delicious, but we thought the stand-out item was the soft shell crab, which kind of looked like a spider roll meets brioche bun.  Lobstah roll only comes cold, and was tasty.  I prefer it hot, but not many restaurants prepare it that way. We were seated at the high top sushi counter, which was a nice location, but would be nice to try the new al fresco dining option next time, which is reclaimed street parking.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Kitchen was out of crab and other seafood no special rolls-   Did not tell us when we sat down did not tell us when we ordered. Came out later and said oops  -  really disappointing  Father‚Äôs Day surprises.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Awesome. Best seafood in the South Bay and one of the Top 3 seafood restaurants in all of LA County

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: So good we will be back again soon!!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Delicious as always!! Thank you!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Amazing food and cocktails!!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love the outdoor tables!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: We enjoyed a lovely ‚Äúsocial distancing‚Äù dinner the other night. The staff went out of their way to accommodate us and even offered a delicious complimentary appetizer while we waited for our table. The food is unbelievably fresh and delicious even though the menu is limited right now, we had no problem finding a variety of delicious options. The cocktails were inventive and the wine selection is carefully curated. Staff is friendly and knowledgeable and chef Alice makes a point to come out to greet the patrons. There is a reason FWD is such a favorite spot. It is well worth the advance reservation and the wait, if it comes to that.

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite
Comments: Love seafood! Fishing with dynamite serves up the best! Oysters , amazing, scallops, sensational. Excellent wine and I‚Äôm in heaven. Have mother but good words about this restaurant. Highly recommend!

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Fishing With Dynamite

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances
Comments: excellent service! love everything!

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

The diners are a good representation of the City, while still retaining its neighborhood feel. Still, the standout  food is the star!

Every dish that came out of the kitchen was perfectly prepared. Hint: order an appetizer or two, and a couple of side dishes, instead of an entre.

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Frances

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: This was a surprise birthday dinner at Gabriel Kreuther.  It was a Monday night and tables were at 30% (perhaps due to the coronavirus?)  There was sophisticated jazz piped in and low decibel level.  The plethora of staff was professional from greet to exit.  GK has two tasting menus: nine course Heritage at $195 and the nine course Chef's Carte Blanche at $245.  While the restaurant recommends you allow 2 hours for the Heritage and 3 hours for the Chef's Carte Blanche, the prior lasted 2:35.   Do not be fooled by the food : time - we left quite satisfied by the portions.It was an amazing dining experience with our favorites being an early course Pistachio encrusted Foie Gras and the Grilled Dock to Dish Tilefish.  Choose from Grilled Berkshire Pork Culotte or Aged Long Island Duck Breast Smoked in Hay as your meat entree.Cocktails of various categories consistent with neighboring Bryant Park range from non-alcoholic, to classics, and signatures.  Pours of wine by the glass were short.As a nice touch, we were presented with a printed menu of the day on exit.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: I prefer to relay my experience at a later date via email.

Name: Gabriel Kreuther
Comments: I've been to GK several times both in the main dining room and lounge.  Both experiences are always special and a cut above other high end restaurants.  We love coming back.

Wine pairing was very good, it didn‚Äôt blow my mind (except for a surprising German Riesling and a phenomenal Chateauneuve du pape) but went very well with food. Price in line with the quality and the Michelin stars, very high but worth it.

I didn‚Äôt want to use mediocre to describe it, as there were some fantastic elements like the Dry aged duck and red apple consomm√© en gel√®e.  Everything else fell flat in my opinion. I just didn‚Äôt think it was worth that kind of money. For a very steep price tag of $1K, every bite should‚Äôve elicited a ‚Äúwow!‚Äù, but it didn‚Äôt. Not to mention from a Michelin rated restaurant at that. To add insult to injury, our server announced at the start of dinner that they have added a dish to their menu which is Risotto and black truffle for an additional $50 pp. We declined, as we‚Äôve anticipated a wonderful evening ahead of us. We couldn‚Äôt have been more wrong.  Spend your hard-earned money elsewhere. Per Se, Jean Georges, and Le Bernardin would be considered reasonable compared to GK, with amazing food to boot. Alinea in Chicago is very much worth the price tag - from start to finish. You would leave on cloud 9 and have the fondest experience ever ( we still dream about it to this day). Comments: Exceptional food and service. We were hot and tired after a long day of hiking and came so close to canceling to eat at the hotel instead. Our server directed us to a few favorites (elk tenderloin and sea bass) and I have to agree with his assessment that the sea bass is the best seafood dish in town. Perfectly balanced umami with a light hand of truffles. So pleased to see an innovative way to prepare sea bass using ramen and mushrooms. The elk was closer to traditional with mashed potatoes and button mushrooms, but so tender it made me a fan again after so many previous tough experiences. Make sure you start with the Curry Cauliflower Bisque (velvety rich but not too much) and Sashimi appetizer. Ambiance was warm with gentle lighting. The prices are on the high end for this town but I‚Äôd go back for the food and service in a heartbeat.
