Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Not sure if it's allowed with COVID ...some small fans would be nice just to keep some air moving ... even at 8:45 at night. Thanks!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: what a wonderful experience- we did outside dining which was wonderful- tables a good 10 feet apart-food was incredible- each course individually was wonderful! would highly recommend-

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The outdoor patio is the most beautiful place for outdoor dining in the entire area.  The gardens are full of fresh vegetables that the chef and staff pick right before serving.  The tomato salad is seasonal and is now available.  The soft shell crabs are stuffed with crabmeat which are seasonal as well.  The gorgeous scenery is only enhanced by fantastic food, wine,  and next to perfect service.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Just lovely, as always.  An enduring reliable favorite.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: As always, we had a wonderful time at L'Auberge Chez Francois.  The food and service were up to the usual excellent standards, and the outside setting was delightful.  We look forward to many more visits in the future, and we recommend this wonderful restaurant to one and all.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It was great!!!  Just as we remembered. We'll be going back soon.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We celebrated my husband‚Äôs birthday with a family lunch.  It was fabulous!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We were seated on the patio and David was our server.  He was energetic and engaged even though the weather was warm.  We have been coming to Chez Francois for many years and will ask for David on our next visit.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We reserved L‚ÄôAuberge after re-opening (due to COVID-19). They cleared the dining rooms and reset it to make sure there are required 6ft distances between tables. They had arranged for all-weather tents in their garden which looks comfortable but we opt to sit inside due to excessive heat. It was a belated birthday lunch since real birthday fell during shutdown. As usual, we had very pleasant experience. Even our known faces chatted with us after such a long time.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Special as always, outstanding food and service.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: L'Auberge is serving the same wonderful food as always and taking social distancing seriously. We ate in a large room with only 6 tables, all well spaced. For most of the night, only one of the other tables was occupied. The excellent staff all wore masks and gloves. We each had the soft-shell crab special as an appetizer (no additional cost) with one lobster entree and one scallop and shrimp entree. The dessert souffle was an good as ever.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We knew this was the place to break our restaurant 'fast'. The outside terrace, completely covered by an open-sided tent, was very pleasant even on a hot day. Tables were spaced far apart and we felt very comfortable. Service, as always, was outstanding. L'Auberge turns even an ordinary lunch with friends into a very special occasion. Merci!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: What a joy to return to the re-opened, if socially distanced, L'Auberge Chez Francois!  From the mushroom crepes to the trout almondine, from the salmon three ways to the tournadoes of beef, we've longed to savor these among our favorite meals and they were as delicious as remembered! (And of course, the little lagniappes, including the addictive garlic toasts and the tart and creamy palate cleansing lemon sorbet delighted our palates and made us smile and feel all was still as it should be at L'Auberge.)  The only thing we missed?  Sharing the space with more happy guests celebrating special occasions!  We look forward to when they can join us again in filling up this beautiful space.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The restaurant had only recently reopened but the experience was almost the same as usual, despite the spaced-out tables and masked wait staff.  They had installed a very large tent outside to accommodate the extra table spacing.  We were inside because it was a very hot day.  However, there were several others outside.  Our reservations were for 5:45 p.m.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Always a great choice for a meal on the patio.  But I'd probably go to Jacques Brasserie next time for lunch.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We went there to celebrate our 20th wedding anniversary - it was wonderful!  We enjoyed ourselves completely!  Service was perfect, great wine and great meal.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: What a wonderful evening dining on the Chez Francois patio. It felt so good to be back enjoying the delicious food, the exceptional service and the beautiful scenery.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: It is the place we celebrate our anniversaries with another couple.  That got postponed due to the Covd-19, but the service is excellent and even more so this time.  The staff seemed genuinely glad to see us.  The food also was excellent, but it is service that makes the overall evening outstanding.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The same wonderful restaurant it has been for more than 60 years!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Our first restaurant dining experience since the quarantine. We were welcome at the door like old friends coming home after a holiday. Ambiance & service were excellent. We recognized some faces behind the mask including Jacques who waved between courses. Desserts are outstanding but my ‚Äúlittle campers in garlic‚Äù (snails) brought back great memories. Merci K&B

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We miss the foods when the father, Monsieur Francois, was the master Chef .

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Delicious food and great service!

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Outstanding, simply outstanding in every way.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Anniversary

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: Outstanding modifications to outside dining due to Covid.  Could not have been more comfortable.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: L'Auberge has recovered from the Corona Virus food and service restrictions to a large decree. The food quality is good again, although the menu is still somewhat restricted. Outdoors they now have a big tent, which is open on the sides. The wine menu is back to normal, which means excellent.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: The management and staff have done a wonderful job re-opening in a way that makes you feel comfortable and safe.  We dined inside due to thunderstorms.  Lovely evening.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: We often visit L'Auberge for special occasions. Today was my wife's 85th birthday. Despite the restrictions caused by the coronavirus, the wait staff was very attentive and the table spacing was sufficient to provide social distancing separation.  As usual, the food was outstanding although the usual small glass of wine has disappeared as part of the fixed price luncheon menu. Not a big thing, but a recognition that things are gradually changing.We look forward to a return visit in August to celebrate our anniversary. If we can find friends or relatives to share the event, we surely will.

Name: L'Auberge Chez Francois
Comments: One of the great experiences in life that is highly recommended

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent as usual.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fantastic! There isn‚Äôt better Italian in Atlanta!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Everything you can ask for a restaurant is in La Grotta!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We had a great experience. The food was phenomenal and the service by Billy our waiter was excellent. Highly recommended

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We had cause for an impromptu family celebration, but wanted to feel safe outside and socially distant. The lovely courtyard at La Grotta was perfect for us. The wait staff was attentive and charming. Thank goodness La Grotta is still here, withstanding the test of time.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: THE BEST food, great service, beautiful ambiance, and our favorite dinner we have had all year! La Grotta is outstanding on all fronts!!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fine food and excellent service in a delightful ambience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Once again the food was excellent. Three of us ordered a dish not even on the menu and it was cooked perfectly. They chefs and staff happily accommodated our off menu request. We can't wait to make reservations and come back soon.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Our family had a wonderful service and experience!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Wonderful experience.  Can't wait to go back. Amazing food and amazing service.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This is our second time dining at La Grotta and the experience never disappoints! The food is superb, the wine list is extensive, and the service is unparalleled! We‚Äôve had Juliano and Danny as our servers and they are true gems!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This was my first experience at La Grotta after many recommendations. The food was phenomenal and the staff was extremely friendly. It took almost 30 minutes past our reserved time to be seated because COVID related reduced capacity.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Delicious meal great service! One of our most favorite places to eat! Treated like family.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: La Grotta never disappoints. The service and food was outstanding. The best mussels and lamb chops in the city. My only complaint was that were were seated next to a very loud party of four outside.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: The experience and food were great. Billy was a great waiter and made sure all of our needs were taken care of.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We‚Äôll be back!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent food and service!!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing Great food. Great service. Superb experienced staff

Name: La Grotta
Comments: This restaurant has been around for over 30 years, and there is a reason for that. Simply put; the best Italian restaurant in Atlanta.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Just was not as good as it has always been Disappointing

Name: La Grotta
Comments: We enjoyed a wonderful meal on the patio.  Both the service and food were excellent.  La Grotta remains one the best values in Atlanta, if not the very best.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: I was extremely happy with my service, food, and atmosphere at La Grotta. Everything was delicious!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Fabulous restaurant. Nice to dine in after months of pick up

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Lovely evening with excellent service and delicious food. So glad La Grotta has reopened. Had the escargot appetizer. Wonderfully creamy and tasty. Cannot wait to go back.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: My favorite restaurant in Atlanta by far!!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing meal. No sign of corona virus here!!  Packed at 8:30 tonight. Everything was great except the service was awful.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Awesome food!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Amazing !!!!  Not too much else to say.  Loved the food and the service, highly recommend.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: The best Italian food in Atlanta.  Service was impeccable.  We celebrated my daughter's 18th birthday, and they treated her like Royalty.  This is as good as it gets in Atlanta for both food and service.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: I have to say that the food was absolutely delicious!  A bit pricey but nonetheless, delicious!  The wait staff was wonderful and very attentive except towards the end of the meal when the place got busier.  I had to flag the waiter down to bring us the check.  I would have wanted the tables to be spaced out a bit further than they were.  During our meal, which was a joyous occasion, there was a lady who was obviously not happy with how things were going at her job and  we got to experience it like we were at her work with her.  She was just loud, obnoxious, and rude.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: I am not one to write reviews unless it was memorable in either direction. It was my second time at La Grotta. Tony was our server - he made us feel very welcomed. Professional, funny and intuitively attentive without ever making us feel rushed or ignored. He made a work dinner a special night. The food was incredible too. If you ever wanted to try quail, this is the place to do it. It was cooked to perfection and the sauce .... oh the sauce!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Pretty great, except the clams which they removed from the bill. Otherwise it was a great meal and experience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Food is excellent with good portion size.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Myvwife and I celebrated our 35th anniversary at La Gtotta and it was a wonderful experience. Great food, superb service and warm atmosphere is a winning combination.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Excellent wine .  Great food and service.  Room was a little loud, but a lot of happy folks tend to make some noise.  Would go again.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: The food was amazing.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Consistent, classic, always a notch above in all arenas!

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Impeccable dining experience.

Name: La Grotta
Comments: Everything was excellent. This is a must place to dine

Name: La Grotta
Comments: WonderfulI have a difficult time picking an entree

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Absolutely incredible in every way. A must go in Maui.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: As always, they did an amazing job!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We had a wonderful time. Everything was enjoyable from the cocktails, to the delicious entrees, and the dessert. The waitstaff were superb. You can tell that they have been well trained.  Kudos to the management.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Awesome meal and fabulous service!!! They treat you like you are the only ones there. Very welcoming and accommodating.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Hands down the best food we had in Maui! We loved it so much we went back for dinner two consecutive nights! They confidently handled my Celiac safe dishes and had numerous GF meals available. LOVE!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Our 4th time coming here in many years...this is the second time we have been here for an anniversary dinner. The fish special was AMAZING.  The wagu ravioli for an appetizer is always good but the sauce is too curling good....get extra bread to clean up every drop of the sauce.  The beet and goat cheese salad was good as well.  Atmosphere is great. Lisa M our waitress was just delightful....great smile fantastic personality.  Just a wonderful experience AGAIN.  Be back next March and do this again.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: I am fortunate to travel to Maui every 2 years. While in Lahaina  I enjoy sitting @ the bar at Lahaina Grill because I am single and the bartenders are very friendly and remember me. At my last visit on 3/16/2020, the owner was there. He made a point to introduce himself as the owner to the couple who sat next to me @ the bar. It was their first time @ the restaurant   He continued visiting many many of the customers at the bar and restaurant area. However, he made no effort to approach me. I felt I wasn‚Äôt a valued patron because I was a single woman.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food and service were excellent. Unfortunately, they have crammed too many tables into the space causing excessive noise and very tight seating areas.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: LƒÅhainƒÅ Grill is terrific. A special experience and amazing food every time. Service by Jillian was top notch.  We are happy to recommend this place, if you know the pricing going in.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: It‚Äôs always such a treat to eat at Lahaina Grill. The staff is wonderful! The food is always exceptional!! And even if we eaten too many rolls( the herb butter can‚Äôt be beat!!),we can‚Äôt pass up the triple berry pie!!! The wine list and cocktails are exceptional too!! Lahaina Grill is one of favorite restaurants on Maui!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Always Fabulous!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We could feel the wonderful ambiance from the minute we entered the restaurant .  The service was outstanding as well as every bit of the food we ordered.  We will definitely go back!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great restaurant.  One half block off water - no ocean view - but excellent food and artwork in dining areas.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: As usual great food and great selection of fine wines. The service was outstanding .

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food was amazing and the service all over was the best!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We were celebrating a birthday and couldn't have asked for a nicer experience. Server Michael, the food, the wine and our birthday pie ... Amazing!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Love the ambience of this restaurant!!Food was delicious and cherry berry pie very good!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Exceptional restaurant with exceptional food and service. We were seated in the quietest area, which was helpful. Otherwise, we would not have been able to hear each other. However, we will be going again this week, right back to table 34!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wonderful experience as always.Everyone‚Äôs meals were fantastic and Lisa our server was spot on!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Michael our server was phenomenal!! Everyone working there went out of their way to chat with us and assist us. Michael even gave us the recipe for the berry pie as well as the penne and meatballs!!!  We can‚Äôt wait to return soon!!!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: This restaurant is charming, and the service is perfect.  We each enjoyed a delicious drink (one alcoholic, one not) and a seafood entree.  Although the food was very tasty, we each felt it should have been warmer.  We were warned that the plates were extremely hot, which they were.  Unfortunately, the food was not.  It wasn't cool enough to merit sending it back, especially since we were there at 5 pm and it was already really busy.  For the high price, however, the food should have been excellent, rather than just very good.  I still rated the restaurant as excellent, however--everything else was terrific.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great service and best food we had our entire vacation. We are both vegetarians and the options did not disappoint.Highly recommended!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wonderful dinner! The food is excellent. Prepared perfectly and presented beautifully. Our server and other staff were super attentive.  Noise level is a bit loud. We will be back!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Another wonderful meal from LG. It's no wonder I come back every time I'm on the island. This time I started with an amazing seared tuna and foie gras plate followed with the opakapaka special. So goooood!! Buddy was a wonderful server, she's a blast. There is just so much warmth about the place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The food was outstanding.  We had the special red snapper, it was absolutely delicious.  The service was excellent as always.  I dine here every time I visit Maui. Highly recommend!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Enjoyed the food and atmosphere.  Staff were excellent.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: The meatballs and the short ribs were awesome and Maui onion soup andMy special birthday berry pie!!!!And Buddy was a character/awesome person took good care of us!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Unquestionably,  this is one of the finest restaurants we have ever dined in. And we have eaten all over the world. Everything was superb - wait staff, food, ambiance, decor, etc.  You are taken care of from the time you enter the restaurant to the time you leave - and if you leave something behind at your table when you leave they will come running after you to make sure you get it back (in my case my hat). The owner goes to each table and introduces himself and makes you really feel at home. This is a top notch organization and the results show it. A real gem!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: 50th anniversary

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Scottie was a wonderful server. Type of place that focuses on the details and treats you with class. Wonderful food.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Wife and I went here after receiving a $100 gift card from my sister.  To be fair, we would never have gone here if not for the gift card after seeing the prices, we just don't dine at expensive restaurants.  Wife had Pacific Salmon ($49) and I had Boneless Short Rib ($46).  Neither of us drink alcohol.  Wife's Salmon was to come with Asparagus, came with String Beans instead.  Waitress and table assistant did come by a bit but nothing special about the service (I would imagine if we got drinks and an appetizer they would have come by more often but not much of a need with just us getting the dinner plate with no desert).  Her Salmon was OK as was my Boneless Rib but nothing special tasting.  Inside was nice but nothing special and a bit noisy even though we weren't in the main dining area.  No place to park close and plan on $10 or more paid parking unless a few blocks away ($5).  Gift card covered the meals, gave a $20 cash tip.  If you like expensive dinners this place may be good with you, check out the cost with the online menu. We much prefer the Okazuya & Deli Honokowai at 3600D Lower Honoapiilani.  If you've never been there go (take cash, they do not accept credit card and closed on Sundays).  Average dinner price is $17-18, the Mahi Mahi (includes two sides) is unbelievably good as is everything on the menu, it's TAKE OUT so it's perfect for beach dinning or at a condo lanai.  Wish sis had given us cash for us to use where we wanted, but her thought was in the right place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Amazing food and service üíï

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Awesome place. Food and service was amazing.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Have been to Maui several times but this is the first time eating here..... everything was awesome! We will be back for sure!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Don‚Äôt miss the Lahaina Grill.  A must while on Maui!

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Went for our anniversary dinner and had asked for a special table, we ate in the middle of the dinning room. The waitress was nice but had a very odd personality that didn‚Äôt seem like she really cares to be there. The tomato in the tomato and mozzarella salad was hard, underripe and had been blanched to peel. Odd. Can‚Äôt believe they can charge so much for one tomato and some cheese! The entrees, one being the special for the day, were a let down as well. Not sure what all the hype is about this place.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: We've enjoyed many evenings at the Lahaina Grill and everyone is special.  Among the many fantastic restaurants in Lahaian and on the island - the Lahaina Grill is our favorite and we believe the best.

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Great food and staff

Name: Lahaina Grill
Comments: Ask for a table away from the bar. Very loud.Wish they could get a better parking experience. There is no handicapped parking near by.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excellent food and service

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Always a Home run of a dining experience. Food and wine are excellent and staff is knowledgeable. My only call out is the server seemed a little annoyed we ordered dessert/dessert wine. Understandably she wanted to close out her tables and go home but otherwise great experience.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Consistently excellent. We brought people who hadn't been there and they were very happy. Service was great, seated promptly, food came out in an orderly and timely manner.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Outstanding as always! Love the new expanded brunch menu and excited that you'll be open for brunch on Saturdays too!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Both the food and the service are consistently good.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Great place. Awesome pasta.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food tasted very nice, only the serving size could have been bigger

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The crudo  was outstanding, the wait staff professional, knowledgeable and friendly.  I was disappointed in the Branzino  it was overcooked and over sauced  and Brussels undercooked; but my husband‚Äôs Halibut  was excellent!  Wine list and wine excellent!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We had a nice brunch, nothing life-changing but good  - the portions are huge though. We ordered way too much - wish the waiter would have told us?!!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Start to finish, the service, suggestions, and presentation were tremendous.  And as for the food?  Again, never missed a single beat, the quail, tuna tartar, spaghetti, there was not a crack in any of the dishes. Finishing with the olive oil cake with creme fraiche was the perfect closure. Bravo to this restaurant that again came through.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing. So hard to get a reservation but l‚Äôartusi was amazing

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing brussel sprouts and french toast. The pasta was good, but a little over priced.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Went for Brunch. Not many true Italian options, not sure anyone on the staff even spoke Italian. Restaurant decor was dated and sloppy. Despite all the stellar reviews we were underwhelmed by the whole experience. Food was good but, pretty standard.  Service was OK.  Didn't make us want to try to get on the list for dinner.  We talked about how disappointed we were the rest of the day.  We'll be going to Rafele from here on out.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Service was a little slow, after the food was delivered - it felt almost like our table was forgotten. It took awhile to get a check (we had to flag down our waiter after the first time we asked for it) and once we put down our credit cards even longer to get back the check to sign. To be fair, they may have been short staffed. It was fairly busy. However that said - when we did get service at the table, everyone was friendly and accommodating. Food was outstanding.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excellent brunch! The pastry basket was filled with delicious homemade treat. Our service was stellar.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food was excellent but was very disappointed with the service. Dined here once before and thought the food was good but was blown away by what I thought was the best service I had ever had. Then this time I went, waited over 20 minutes past my reservation time, server was inattentive and the gap between appetizer and entree was far too long. Food was good but poor service overshadowed it this time.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We had a reservation at 8:30 and they sat us at 9. They gave us a glass of champagne as an apology which was nice. Otherwise the experience was great, server was knowledgeable. Food was good but did not exceed expectations.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food here is amazing, especially the pasta, but the ambience and service have suffered from the popularity of the place. Still overall one of my favorite restaurants in Manhattan.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We have been several times to this restaurant for dinner, this was our second time for brunch and we were so displeased with the service and how much they rushed us through our meal. It was a late brunch reservation and they cut off service because they had to get ready for the dinner crowd. My recommendation is not to allow customers to make late brunch reservations if the service level is diminished  because they have to turn over for dinner.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Great service and an even better meal!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Delicious as always - highly recommend sharing the Lemon Ricotta pancakes on the side :) Were very accommodating when we were late for a reservation despite a busy brunch time!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Excelente Service! Amazing food!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Food was great, service was awful. Got orders wrong, took a long time to check on us. Would still go back though!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: My boyfriend & I LOVE L‚ÄôARTUSI !!! We always are trying new spots but this is a place we will forever love and continue to return to regularly ü•∞

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Everything was delicious and the service was great. The spaghetti was really light and fresh. Roasted potatoes are a must as is the olive oil cake!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: It was our first year anniversary each plate was delicious

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing pasta. Delicious meal. Cant wait to go back

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Wow ‚Äî stellar food and service and not a fortune

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Lovely restaurant and food but difficult to get a reservation

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Amazing experience from the service to the food. If you can get a reservation I highly recommended.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Clearly this is a very popular restaurant but to my mind, it is overrated. The dishes we ate that night were overseasoned with far too much emphasis on chili in every dish. The steak was ordered medium rare but was served rare and I know we could have sent it back but this would have disrupted the evening. The tables are too close together and the noise level was rising even though the restaurant had only just opened.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: One of our favorites!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Always incredible.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Phenomenal food and absolutely amazing service. Our waiter went above and beyond to make our first l‚Äôartusi experience amazing. Food is insanely good.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Love love love L'Artusi. This place knows what it's doing. It has amazing food and the best, nicest, most competent waitstaff and management. In a city with so many good restaurants, this is the one I go back to again and again as my favorite.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: It still seems de rigeur for city restaurants to court noise level beyond the ears of most human diners.  That said, L‚ÄôArtusi was a wonderful culinary experience, with a thoughtful sommelier who was touchingly unaffected, and a waiter with a sense of irony.  The butter lettuce salad was a marvel, the pasta (kale pyramide) far from the ‚Äúpile of greens‚Äù its name tends to imply to Americans.  That we were the oldest diners in evidence is certainly not a complaint...just a regret for lost dining innocence!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: We came for our anniversary and the service was amazing! We had a 10pm reservation but popped in around 7 and they were able to seat us early right away. They provided complimentary champagne at the start which was special and thoughtful. Our waiter Dan was perfectly attentive, helping with recommendations and kept the speed of the meal at a relaxing, welcoming pace. The experience overall was one I can‚Äôt wait to recommend to others! We will be back!

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Was very good! Food was delicious. Minus 1 star for the noise level

Name: LArtusi
Comments: The food is always great here! It is a special place because my fianc√© and I ate here before he proposed to me in April. The food is so good that we have come back just because and to bring visiting friends and family.

Name: LArtusi
Comments: Unfortunately the hangar steak this time was not up to the usual lartusi standards. It was tough and not just one piece but all of it. So disappointed. I have been here 5 times before with no issue. Plan to go back again and try it. Made the whole dinner a fail for a new guest.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Used to come to Le Dip fairly regularly, but this was the first time since the pandemic that we'd come.  We had a table on the patio, and it was perfect.  Le Dip, as always, does a great job of making you feel like you are truly in Paris.  The food was amazing, the ambiance was great (If anything, it was easier than it used to be to talk here), and they did a great job of socially distancing the tables. The tuna carpaccio and the warm shrimp salad  were great to start with, the trout amandine and steak frites were perfect, and of course, you have to have the profiteroles to round out the meal.  The only thing was the hostess was pretty rude, but we just chalked it up to adding to the French feel.  Our server, Nabil, was fun and made recommendations we did not regret taking.  Overall, Le Dip is a classic and reliable part of the DC food scene, and covid hasn't changed that!

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Le Dip still hasn't lost its friendliness and sparkle and Francophile hipness, even in the era of masks and social distancing. The tuna carpaccio appetizer is a must, as are goug√®res if you're not already filled up on bread. Also love the steak frites and roast chicken--you'll want to order a second side of the impossibly buttery mashed potatoes for dessert! Not a fan of the mushroom tart app: it's a lot of dry puff pastry topped off with mushrooms.

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: I love Le Diplomate. The food is always good (I always get the warm shrimp salad), the bread is great, and the service is professional and quick. I felt very safe in their spaced out, outdoor dining, and appreciated the measures taken to ensure safety. Their wine/drink list is a little limited, likely due to the pandemic, but otherwise, it's one of my favorite restaurants!

Name: Le Diplomate

Name: Le Diplomate
Comments: Note that we dined at Le Diplomate during social distancing--well less than 50% capacity inside.  Normally it is not a quiet place. We ate inside; they also have tables outside, but at 90 degrees inside was better.My choices: warm shrimp salad and trout with almonds.  Salad was phenomenal, due to perfectly cooked shrimp and ripe avocado along with the greens. Trout was perfect. Spouse had foie gras pate, incredibly smooth, and the Tuesday night lobster risotto special.  Both really good--lobster cooked perfectly.  Splurged on an expensive bottle of white Burgundy.  Perfect with these dishes.When restaurants open fully, Le Diplomate will return to being packed.  Good for them, even though that means it will again be tough to get a reservation.  (We dined on a Tuesday night with reservations a week in advance.)

Comments: Above and beyond anything that could have been expected. After visiting Peasant, and meeting and talking with Chef Forgione (and being absolutely blown away by the food) only a week ago for my first dating anniversary with my boyfriend, I decided to take him here for his birthday. We were treated like royalty from the second we walked in, and the food matched the service. We ordered the chicories salad to start. It may sound/seem simple, but that was one of the best salads we‚Äôve ever had. We were also given the Hiramasa tartare dish, which my boyfriend declared the best tartare dish he‚Äôs ever had. I had the half chicken (cooked under a brick), and he had the halibut - both outrageous. We had the carrot cake for dessert, but we were also given what the waiter called, ‚ÄòThe Egg.‚Äô He basically told us to move back in our seats a bit as he proceeded to toss a white chocolate egg filled with passion fruit into a plate ... it was as hysterical as it was delicious, and my boyfriend does not like passion fruit. There are no words that can properly describe this experience. From the card my boyfriend received when he sat down wishing him a happy birthday from the restaurant to the desserts to the sparkling wine to the everything bagel amuse bouche to the amazing atmosphere, this was a one of a kind experience. Simply outrageous, and we will be back.

Comments: My husband and I had dinner at Marcel‚Äôs before attending a performance at the Kennedy Center. We opted for the theater menu. It was one of the nicest meals we have had in DC in a while. Service was great, and not just by DC standards. The food was excellent, as well. They even have a complementary car service to the Kennedy Center. I would definitely go back again, and we will certainly make this our go to dinner spot before heading the KC.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We had a fabulous evening at Marcel's. The service from the front of the house was perfectly balanced between attentiveness and discretion. The food was beautifully prepared and presented and delicious in every way. Marcel's is elegant and we enjoyed the evening very much. What is Musak everywhere else is a the gentle jazz piano in the bar at Marcel's. The perfect atmosphere for a special evening. Recommended.Two items that detracted somewhat, but never interfered. There appeared to be some tension between the wait staff and the support staff - maybe just the usual search for perfection but we overheard more than one impatient comment. Second, for a prix fixe menu offering we were surprised there was no option for wine pairings and when we asked if one could be provided received a frustrated response that sure, we could do that if you wanted. That said, the pairing were from the wine-by-the-glass menu and were splendid!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Always an exceptional experience. We had the 4-course menu option and sat at the bar before our show at the Kennedy Center. We loved all our dishes - I had the black cod, salmon, and lobster timbale. The poached pear dessert was delightful. Highly recommend!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This was our second time; it won't be our last. Jonathan is the epitome of five-star service, perfectly paired with Chef Robert's exquisitely delicious and beautifully presented dishes. The dining room is an oasis of peace away from the noise of this area. Gentle jazz and live piano play softly. Sight, sound, smell, taste, texture - Marcel's perfectly attends to every sense. There is a reason Marcel's is in Tom Sietsema's Hall of Fame for DC dining. We look forward to our next experience at Marcel's.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Another enchanting evening at Marcel‚Äôs - a wonderful dinner with great service.  The creativity never stops.  There is always something new to try.  And Marcel‚Äôs will always accommodate food allergies without compromising quality.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We had an excellent time - food, presentation, service, atmosphere all exceeded expectations.  It was one of the few top-notch restaurants where you can have a decent conversation.  Yes, you pay for that privilege (tables aren't crammed together) but it was surprisingly reasonable given the quality of the experience.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We are coming back within two weeks of our first visit. It is rare to have a nice place live up to expectations, but Marcel's did. My husband said this was his favorite meal since we went to French Laundry, and that was about a year-and-half ago of regular restaurant going (West Coast and DC).  We go out to eat a fair amount in all price ranges and in this range, once expects more than just good food. We got great food and great service executed by professionals, not just folks who want to wait tables for a couple years before they move on to their "real job". And, yes, it is not a bargain dining hall, but we felt it was a good value for the quality, portions,  presentation, and vibe (great jazz pianist in the lounge, complimentary swank ride to the Kennedy Center for show). Plus, the wines by the glass were priced very accessibly and tasted like much more expensive price points. If you appreciate a more traditional fine dining experience with professional, adult staff and are tired of dropping a couple of bills only to see everyone around you dressed like slobs, make your next date at Marcel's.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Excellent special occasion location. Great food and service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We have been dining here for 5 years. Always had a great meal.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: I took my wife for our 29th anniversary and I wasn‚Äôt sure what i was get into.But then. The show stared. Amazing food. The unique taste of each plate, was unreal. Henry the waiter. 5 stars. And then i had the honor to meet David. Not just an amazing chef. A true gentleman. I don‚Äôt know when i will go back. But for sure i will

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Food was delicious and service, exceptional.  We were within hearing distance of the pianist in the bar; loved that!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: We have been to the fine dining room a number of times and love it.  We were eager to try the Bar special menu.  Our reaction was that the food was fabulous.  However the amount was  on the small side and the wine pairing was minuscule.  There was no dessert included.  We were sort of in and out in a short time.  Generous on the bread service.We would not go back for the bar experience but would go back to the fine dining room.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This wasn't just dinner out--this was a dining experience. Go when you can take your time and enjoy being pampered by the service, wowed by the presentation and flavors and relaxed by the elegant ambiance.  It'll be the  kind of evening that you'll talk about for a long time.  I can't imagine rushing through dinner here to get to the theater but I guess people do. I didn't want to leave. The food was amazing. There used to be a Washington Post food critic, Donald Dressden (goes way back) I think his name was--when he went to a great restaurant he said the "food sang" yep, the food sings here, like Pavarotti on a plate, or something.  You have to go, save up your birthday, anniversary, special occasion or just 'cause you deserve it and spend it here.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This restaurant is without doubt one of the top in the DC area if not the country. My only regret is that I did not try it earlier. The staff - from the owner to the waiters to all who assisted us - were kind, punctual, caring, and welcoming. The chef and cooking staff really know what they are doing and the food is sourced fresh and of highest quality. We ordered from a tasting menu from which one could choose four, five, or six dishes. We chose four, which was more than adequate. Among the three of us we had salad, fish including shellfish, venison, pasta, and several desserts, inter alia. The vegetables were fresh and the cooking afforded succulent, wonderful tasting options. The wine selections ranged from reasonable to pricy, and we were able to get a bottle of a recommended red wine by the glass that was excellent, from a vineyard and vintage that we knew. Expect to pay twice what you would a most high end restaurants but the result will be more than twice as good. I was reminded of an Inn in the countryside in Virginia that has great food, but Marcel's is  better and less expensive. We'll definitely be back!

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: A perfect evening from the impeccable service to the menu choices to the presentation and taste of each course.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Wonderful complete dinner- all aspects were first rate - Vinny took exceptional time care of my wife and I

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: This is a wonderful French restaurant with smart service, a creative and skilled chef and a lovely wine list. Each dish has deep roots in traditional French haute cuisine that have been married expertly to our time. It is the perfect place for a special occasion.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Highly recommended.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Marcel's has always been one of the best dining experiences for us. We were there for our Anniversary last weekend. We told our waiter/host Mark that we wanted a picture with Chef Wiedemier for our Anniversary and he came through for us. Mark took great care of us ... very professional, attentive, good natured. Like talking to a friend. Mark loves his job and it shows. We especially enjoyed the Foie Gras, lobster appetizer, sea bass, but everything was a foodie treat. Ambiance is classy and even though restaurant was almost full, it was not noisy and you could enjoy having a nice conversation in a soft voice (a rarity nowadays in restaurants).

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: The service was top notch, which you would expect for a restaurant of this caliber.  The presentation of the food was wonderful and the flavors were distinct and exceptional. The tasting menu was right-sized and  perfect for the amount of courses chose. (Four).  The wine pairings were well thought out.  Overall a wonderful experience.  A call out to our head waiter Adam.  Spot on service.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: One of the top French restaurants in Washington.  A traditional, delicious menu--no foam-filled balloons.   Just great food beautifully prepared and served.

Name: Marcel's by Robert Wiedmaier
Comments: Impeccable service and a wonderful wine list. The best parts of the menu are the starters ( scallops, boudin Blanc consomm√©) but the duck entre was average.This restaurant is heart attack expensive and I would have expected better.

Name: Marea
Comments: Great all around!

Name: Marea
Comments: I wish I could give it 6 stars. This place is a gem.Food and service are outstanding. Excellent wine list.

Name: Marea
Comments: We had a fantastic evening. Staff were gracious, professional and attentive. Dishes were excellent. Looking forward to returning soon.

Name: Marea
Comments: Fabulous gluten free pasta   I loved the truffle and anchovy sauce. Perfection.

Name: Marea
Comments: As always amazing!

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea is an elegant restaurant from the decor to the food to the service. Great attention is paid to every detail to make the experience luxurious and special. We were there for a birthday lunch starting with excellent cocktail and wine (don‚Äôt miss the delicious bread as it‚Äôs brought around) into appetizers of a variety of crudi (thinly sliced raw fish) and entrees of halibut and steak. We ordered sorbet for dessert then were pleasantly surprised with a special birthday dessert plus cookies and small tiramisu portions. All were excellent and beautiful. Adding to the overall atmosphere is the elegant china, cutlery, glassware and serving pieces. Dining here made it an occasion.

Name: Marea
Comments: Always perfect! Best place in New York

Name: Marea
Comments: My husband and I enjoyed an amazing dinner at Marae last Sunday. We treated ourselves to the five course tasting menu with the wine pairing. Everything was delicious, especially the halibut and the Tagliatelle with a sauce made from bone marrow. The chocolate dessert balls were also scrumptious.  Each wine paired nicely with its dish. The service was exceptional. We shall definitely return and hope the Tagliatelle is on the menu that night.

Name: Marea
Comments: It was perfect and my 2-yr old daughter really enjoyed the food as well as the setup.  Really appreciated it.

Name: Marea
Comments: The atmosphere and the wait staff are absolutely stupendous! The food however, ranges from good to very good. Nothing reached a level of excellence. At these astronomical prizes, I would expect to be blown away by every morsel.Certain dishes were cooked perfectly and we're quite tasty, however others seem to be overcooked. (Not a good thing with seafood.) Parts of the grilled octopus we're just downright dry tough. Regarding the Brodetto, The broth, while absolutely delicious, was served warm to start with and cooled to room temperature by the end of the dish.If you are looking for calm, culture, civility, this place is it. If, however, you were looking simply for amazing food, you may find yourself a little disappointed. Overall, a lovely dining experience with a phenomenal wait staff, but I just wish the food had lived up to the rest of the experience.

Name: Marea
Comments: 3rd visit and every meal outstanding! Pointless to explain just to! Not stuffy like most restaurants of this caliber

Name: Marea
Comments: Great place for lunch!  Great menu and beautiful space!

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Prix Fixe lunch @ $67 or will offer a la carte.  Very good tuna crudo, tatare.  Very good pastas ( garganelli, Agnolotti).  Attentive service. Quite expensive for lunch.

Name: Marea
Comments: Marea always is outstanding ‚Äî wonderful good quality and service.   It is expensive, however.

Name: Marea

Definitly if your kids are not too loud ( my son Definitly was so i gave him my phone to keep entertained) it‚Äôs a definit must go restaurant for food, comfort, and that finesse touche.

Name: Marea

We thoroughly enjoyed each dish, mostly consisting of exquisite seafood and specialty pasta, paired with some fabulous wines.  My partner stayed with the white wine accompaniments while I enjoyed the lighter reds that were selected.  Service was outstanding, and there was still an air of romance at the corner booth despite it being 230 in the afternoon!  Marea will be on our calendar every time we visit the Big Apple!

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Name: Marea

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: One of the best meals I‚Äôve had. Creative dishes. Friendly attentive wait staff.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: We went to Market to celebrate my wife's birthday. Market is one of our favorite restaurants. The food is always great. The decor of the restaurant is lacking (needs a refresh) but the food is amazing. We both did the tasting menu and I have to tell you it ranks up there with the few times I've eaten at Addison. Since the portions are bigger at Market I would say it was my best dining experience in the 5 years we have lived in San Diego. We will certainly visit again but really wish they gave the place a face lift.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: Great meal.  Food was excellent.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar
Comments: The ‚Äúcomplimentary valet‚Äù is a confusing concept... you still want to tip the valet, but who carries cash these days? So just be prepared to bring cash so you can tip the valet.Hostess was not warm, as a hostess should be. However, the waiters were exceptional! Thank you. Very friendly. I don‚Äôt think management should require them to memorize specials of the day, as it comes across very rehearsed, awkward, and off-putting. Save them the embarrassing stress & just write it on a simple menu card. I love a dark, cozy ambiance & this place is that exactly. The food was good but I noticed on the tasting menu the same base sauces and ingredients were repeated a few times. If you don‚Äôt like salmon, don‚Äôt order the trout... it tastes identical. The Cabernet braised short rib was insanely delicious. I was accidentally given a restaurant week menu & the manager was kind enough to honor the discounted prices on the menu I was presented with. Thank you. Very generous gesture.Some of the side panel wood near my table was very dusty (attention to cleanliness details always appreciated), and there were a few annoying gnats buzzing around that I had to keep swatting away & this interfered with my relaxed dining mood.

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar

Name: Market Restaurant and Bar

The dining room is set up nicely and (kudos) for once no stupid tables.  The place was busy but the noise level moderate!!  Food overall was excellent - an interesting take on a tuna tartar,  excellent corn soup with smoked port.  Entr√©es were trout, duck and beef tenderloin - all very well prepared - portions very adequate.  Desserts yummy.  Attentive, efficient and polite service!!!!Bar selection OK - not really great and along with the wine list insanely overpriced.  A clear indication that they are catering to the Rancho Santa Fe crowd. In all a very enjoyable evening and will visit again when in the area
