We had to ASK our waiter for a refill of our water glasses and then nobody actually did it until we finally stopped a suit clad higher functionary who actually did the work himself.  Staff training is needed (as is an attitude adjustment).

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: While waitstaff is polite and knowledgeable, they were slow during a midday rush.  Perhaps too few people for the guest load.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food and the service was outstanding!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: After so many years, the Modern has maintained its high standard with food, service and ambience! Its a reliable place to go back to!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The atmosphere, the service, and the food make this our favorite place to eat in New York.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great casual place. The food is creative and delicious, the service was great.I highly recommend it.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: I have dined at the Modern Bar room dozens of time-never had a bad meal-you can't go wrong if you decide to eat there and it is also very popular for just drinks.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great food

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Everything was great. The setting, the food and the wait staff. We had a lovely evening. Will definitely visit again

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great as always!!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: With the MOMA renovations causing closure of the art museum temporarily, we had to skip our annual visit. However, the Bar at the Modern was available so we were able to enjoy a marvellous Saturday lunch.  Service was skilled and our waiter was very well informed on the options and preparation details. Every course of our three course meal was amazing in taste and presentation.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: I cannot believe the huge disappointment I experienced at The Bar at the Modern, which has been one of my favorite spots in NYC since it opened...we even celebrated there the day of the birth of our first grandson eleven and a half years ago...and I always want friends visiting us in NYC to meet us at The Bar at the Modern.I brought a friend who had never been to the restaurant for lunch, specifically to try the tart d'alsace.This was a new food for her...when this rectangle that looked like a slice of pizza arrived I was shocked.That is not a tart d'alsace,  I thot...it had a lot of red and green in it...not the creamy white I was accustomed to...and the taste was unidentifiable...my friend said all she could taste was salt.  I did not complain...at least I thot the tart was edible, but could not explain the taste.My baby gem lettuce salad was ok,  but not as lovely as I expiated, to the eye and the tongue.My friend was aghast that the soup of the day cost 24 dollars, but she ordered it as she was not very hungry (we lunched early...ll:45 )...I was so devastated that I considered, and still am ,  writing directly to Danny Meyer.  He would be horrified had he been at our table yesterday Aug 30. I will not be returning to The Modern, unless an explanation is given.  I can get a beautiful tart d'alsace at BENOIT, as I did on Aug l9...the size of the tart was generous and share - able with 5 other people at my table for drinks and small plates...the size of the MODERN's tart was not even enough for two.Ah well..in the big picture of life I can handle such a disappointment.  But this indeed feels like a loss of one of my favorite places in NYC.Patricia Lahrmer Ross on Aug 3l 20l9

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great service, fantastic food, highly recommend

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Great dinner!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The overall experience was top notch.  This proved to be a perfect choice for the night.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food and service at the Modern Bar Room were excellent.  I was also struck by the quality and presentation temperature of the wines by the glass.  Many restaurants in nyc serve very poor wines by the glass kept at the wrong temperature.  This was not at all the case at the Modern - the wine was excellent.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The food is so high quality and the tastes explode in the dish. The crispy salmon was tremendous.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: We had an amazing meal here, and it really made me want to experience the main dining room someday. My spouse and I each ordered the three course tasting menu, choosing an appetizer, entree, and dessert. I had the wine pairings as well, while he ordered a Manhattan.  Every single thing I ate was perfect. My very favorite was the charred avocado with peekytoe crab. The flavors and textures of that dish will stay with me for a long time to come. I cannot recommend it highly enough. My spouse started with the corn soup, which I had almost ordered. It was very tasty, but nowhere near as good as the avocado. The service was very attentive, with our water frequently refilled and being checked in with regularly. The time between courses might have felt long if you were in a hurry or very hungry, but for us it was the perfect pacing. The room definitely has a lively atmosphere, which is nice, though the tables are quite close and it was hard to tune out the conversation at the table next to us.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The bartenders were very attentive and demonstrated great mixology Skills as well as menu knowledge.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Caesar was just an amazing service provider - his suggestions were spot on and so was the service provided by every other member  at this restaurant, thank you for making a huge difference in the way you treat your guests.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Food was terrific.  Staff was very accommodating.  However the room smelled of fresh paint.  That is very unappetizing.  Perhaps the restaurant should close on days when it is freshly painted.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: As always a most pleasurable dining experience. The wine list is extraordinary as are the prices with only a handful below triple digits.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Fabulous restaurant week menu ...we both had the salmon that was cooked to perfection. Service was excellent...waiter/waitresses friendly and professional..

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: The ambiance, door and service were spot on. The ‚Äòannouncement‚Äô of each dish was over the top and unnecessary, particularly when some of the dishes were repetitive from one diner to the next. It seemed silly and disingenuous. $18 for a glass of white wine had us passing on spirits at lunch. It would have been nice for the iced tea drinker and the coffee drinkers to be offered seconds for the price of $7.00 for an iced tea and $6.00 for a cup of Joe. It‚Äôs the little things...

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Perfection!  Fabulous food, great service, lovely ambience.  Can't wait to go back :)

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Was visiting this place twice during a restaurant week.  Amazing a nd delicious food, great service!!! Thank you!!!!

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Fantastic! Wait staff excellent. Picked two course restaurant menu for lunch. Amazing salmon and cavatelli dishes. Cocktails sublime. Also, the modern is a no tip establishment but you wod never know it, the service was impeccable.  Only negative was we had planned on going next door to MOMA but its closed until mid October.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: We really like and enjoyed the service and the food! We go to upscale restaurants sometimes. This one is at the top of the list of the restaurants we went in terms of the food taste. Highly recommend.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Service was very nice and sweet. Food is of great quality and value. Went there for the restaurant week but will certainly go back again.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: This was a terrific evening made all the better by the attentiveness of Maitre d' Michele Molier.  I had managed to put our reservation on the calendar for the incorrect date.  We showed  up a day early and could not have returned on the next night.  Michele  led us to the bar and then went to work finding us an  table.  Shortly we were escorted to an ideal table for memorable dinner.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Disappointing from start to finish. We have come to value the Modern on our ‚ÄúA‚Äù List of fine cuisine. We selected the Restaurant Week offerings. Servers lacked adequate knowledge of the vintages. ‚ÄúShort‚Äù pours dominated. The Main course was bland and tasteless. Two slices of bread were an additional charge. Rather insulting. Wine pairings were delayed with food arrival. The meal was rushed although there was ample seating. Our servers were not attentive. The only redeeming part was the support table staff. The Modern has been always exceptional. Unfortunately this experience falls into the ONE STAR category ... at best.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Wonderful time. Everything is perfect from start to finish.

Name: The Modern - Bar Room and Dining Room
Comments: Exquisite!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Outstanding food and service.  If you like tasting menus it doesn't get much better.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely fantastic. Food and staff were both amazing.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: What a great experience. Nice staff, amazing food, and a good wine pairing.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely amazing experience. Highly recommend it if you‚Äôre looking for a treat. The atmosphere is lovely.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The entire experience from start to finish was excellent. We were there celebrating a special event, the staff made special arrangements for us and brought in some items from outside vendors for us. Food and service was top notch, chefs were engaging energetic, friendly and professional. I cannot emphasize enough how on top of their game this group, both front of house and chefs are. Actually what comes to mind when thinking about our experience is how impressed we were with the entire team. Tasting menu was off the charts as were the drink pairings. We are not from the New York region so do not know when we will be back, however the evening is one that we will always remember. A special thanks to the entire crew for a magical evening!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great food, great service. Highly recommend doing the wine pairing. A great night :)

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Excellent all around. It deserves the 2 Michelin stars that it has.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The entrance was hard to find, but located in an alley. Astoundingly delicious meal. Service was top notch. We would gladly return.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Goes without saying. This place is among the most amazing tables in the world. Eating at Ko is equivalent to receive a doctor's prescription, have a major update about taste and receive a masterclass about service, all in the same time.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Super!!!!Ich liebe es!!!!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service, what more could you ask for?!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Wonderful food paired with excellent wine.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The most memorable tasting menu experience! Excellent food, non-pretentious and focused on intense flavours. Loved the relaxed setting and impeccable service. #PartyInMyMouth

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: We had a fantastic dinner. The flavor combinations were innovative and incredible. The service was wonderful. Not only were they attentive, but they engaged with our questions and made us feel like they cared what we thought. We also went to Le Bernardin and Eleven Madison Park on this trip and Ko was our favorite of the three.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Everything was wonderful.Food and wine pairings were excellent.My only gripe was the lack of detailed explanations on one or two courses of the tasting menu. But at that point, I'm just splitting hairs.Overall, I had a fantastic experience.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of the greatest eating experiences I have ever had. I am a loyal listener and follower of David Chang and this was my very first time to experience one of his restaurants.My sister took me for my 60th birthday. I truly was not ready for such a great experience . The staff was so engaging and connected with my sister and me beyond anything I had ever experienced before in a restaurant. I tell everyone that I would not order anything we had on a menu , but everything was delicious and so much part of the experience.  We had listened to the pod cast that day about Ko and we had so many questions (need to meet Sean and Sue) . The person who worked with us truly connected and kept adding to our experience.  We asked about the Japanese Cheese Cake mentioned in the pod . She told us she could not get it for us - They it appeared with a candle in it. You should know that we posted on Face book and you are going to get a lot of new people . If its David Chang we are in

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Momofuku Ko was an incredible experience.  We got to sample things we most likely never would have eaten if it wasn't for this night.  Service is exemplary, and the food is Incredible.  We also enjoyed the Alcohol Pairing.  Be prepared for an expensive night out, but one you will never forget.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great food  and pairing

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Everything was perfect from start to finish.   Loved the playlist üé∂

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: I had a great time with my girlfriend celebrating Valentine‚Äôs Day week.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Food was okay. Wine was great. Service was good. We went for the tasting menu and it went on for 3 hours through no fault of our own, and they asked to move us for the next people. That was absolutely wild to me. Not worth the $1,000 we paid.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Impeccable food and service! Well worth the splurge for a special occasion. We look forward to returning for our next anniversary, and will be visiting the bar in the meantime!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Loved it!  All of the good things about a pretentious tasting menu (impeccable service, delicious food made with great ingredients) with none of the pretense. It was casual, fun, and laid-back but definitely still something special. Highly recommend!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: They were trying to do sushi and wagyu yakiniku, but when it's so easy to find authentic Japanese restaurants in NYC with chefs from Japan with years of experience, I felt like their attempts were not quite successful. Given that the majority of their courses were very much focused around the Japanese cuisine, I would probably just go to a Japanese restaurant.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Great ambiance. Nice to sit at the counter and watch the meals' preparation. Very interesting creations/compositions, most of the 12 dishes are a success  (sea urchin and chickpea puree, what?!) and only a couple of "disappointments" (seabass only "so so" / "whatever" ...). Enjoyed drinking sake too. No surprise with the bill with the unique menu (and service is included)

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Semplicemente tutto TOP...Grazie ragazzi di tutto.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: A wonderful experience - a combination of creativity, great service and a comfortable ambience.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: such thoughtful and imaginative food in a welcoming ambiance. I go once a year, but was greeted as a regular, my champagne choice was remembered, had enjoyable, non fake chats with chefs and the manager. Such fun to watch the chefs and wait each surprise. Nearly always perfect balance of tastes and texture. Umami often, acid balance, little spikes of salt. My favorite NYC meal!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: The 4 hour lunch was a fabulous gastronomic adventure - priced a bit higher than where I think it  should be, but still quite an experience!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: An exceptional dining experience. Got to try foods and wines that I'd never have had access to otherwise. The preparation and experience were elegant but didn't alienate me as the guest. A must-do for anyone that takes food seriously.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of the best meals I‚Äôve ever had. Granted I don‚Äôt eat like this often, but if I had the money I‚Äôd do it again. It was a once in a lifetime opportunity for me and I‚Äôd do it again, in an instant.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: David Chang does not cook here. It‚Äôs the farm team - everyone is working hard and professionally - and seems about 23 years old.Specified a pescatarian menu in response to management‚Äôs solicitation some days in advance.  At the resto a chef asked ‚ÄúWhat do you think of duck?‚Äù  I think duck is not a fish.The place is maybe fine for tourists but not for NYC locals looking to be wowed.  It delivers neither the wizardry of an Alinea nor the solid reliability of a Le Bernardin.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing. If you‚Äôre thinking about going - don‚Äôt hesitate just do it

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Very personable and knowledgeable staff! The tasting menu is an intricate blend of flavors, decadence, and most importantly texture. A must visit!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: One of my best dining experiences! Thank You so much to the team at Momofuku KO for making me fool so at home and looked after me sooo well! I HIGHLY recommend a meal here!!!! The Rice Cream should be permanently on the menu... just saying!!!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: This was one of the best meals I have ever eaten!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Unbelievable experience. Amazing food and attentive and warm service. The people there are the best!

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Amazing meal every time. Must do "wine" pairings, which includes other drinks besides wines. Sit at the counter. Cooking can be a spectator sport.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Absolutely wonderful experience throughout.

Name: Momofuku Ko
Comments: Yule present to each other.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: This is one of our favorites  in Dallas! Always consistent and delicious

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Excellent food. Very safe. Everything is very spaced out and clean.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We loved our evening at NHS! From the green chili crab dip to the halibut special to my husband's cheeseburger, every single food item we ordered was delicious. Service was great, pacing of food was appropriate, and it wasn't too loud. The only fault we found was no highchair for my 7 month old niece.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: It was a birthday celebration and they said ‚Äú happy birthday‚Äù! Thought they should have brought out a dessert....

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Marques was the best, total professional and so personable. Food was fantastic. Thanks.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always the safest place and best of food, service and drinks!!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Great job with socially distancing and masked staff.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Our server was fantastic!  Wish our table wasn't right in front of the kitchen though.  We had a great time and the food was amazing.Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Fabulous as always, from the ambience and service to the food. My favorite!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Best food! Best service!!  Love this restaurant!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Everything was outstanding. The service & food were fantastic

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Excellent service and amazing food!!  The staff made us feel very comfortable. We can‚Äôt wait to go back!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Been eating here for years and EVERYTHING is delicious!  I always go for the fish special because its always fantastic.  Hubby loves the Fish & Chips.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: First time back since the re-opening and it was very good. Staff and service was excellent, they followed safe distance and hygiene protocol as required.  All the food was terrific, one exception being the pasta special, which had overcooked sauce with a burned bottom of the pan taste to it and the noodles were undercooked-to the point of being a bit stiff. Overall very pleased that one of our favorite places is open and will only get better!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We were there to celebrate my husband‚Äòs 35th birthday. Everything was spot on, from the service to the food to the drinks. We really appreciated how seriously they took social distancing and Covid precautions. Will definitely be back again soon! Have already recommended to my friends who are leery about going out to restaurants right now.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Favorite place in Dallas!!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We had an amazing night here this week! Can‚Äôt wait to go all the time now !

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food was delicious as always, and wonderful service.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Fun atmosphere, great service, and outstanding food.  Will definitely make this one a regular stop.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Knocked it out of the park in the new norm with safe environment, service and best food in the city-dare I say world right now!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always a favorite!  Food and Service was outstanding!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: When we arrived they were closed yet we had a confirmed reservation. It‚Äôs a great place. We will try again.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: It was closed when we arrived. we‚Äôve eaten here many times and it is Excellent!  But so disappointed to arrive to a locked door and no notice.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Last time we were at NHS prior to the stay at home order and it was as good as it always is. I miss it so much! GM Julia is always so helpful and accommodating with my dairy allergy and we had Marcus as our waiter who kills it every time. My boyfriend and I cannot wait until our next visit! Miss you guys so much.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: As always, the best place in Dallas!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: The schnitzel, fried chicken and fish were all delicious. Good drinks too.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: A wonderful dining experience each and every time! Make sure you book your reservation early as this hot commodity books up! Though you can always eat at the bar where Rob and Alex will take excellent care of you!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Great vibe and great food.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food and waiter were very good.  Felt rushed as the restaurant became busier and they wanted to turn the tables.  It is really the only negative I would say about the restaurant.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: The hostess Emily makes every visit special! We will be back soon!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: A wonderful dining experience!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always great food, service and ambiance.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Same as usual - excellent.Waiter was outstanding and had everything covered without being intrusive.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: We were celebrating our friends recent engagement (haven‚Äôt seen them since) and we chose NHS to treat them as a surprise. I‚Äôd put in the comments of the reservation we were hoping for a nice table or booth to celebrate this night out. Instead, we were placed right in front of the noisy, highly trafficked kitchen. We felt that the service was rushed the entire time, from when we first sat down and were asked if we want to put in an order for food before our drink orders were taken to when our water glasses were stripped from the table. Also, we had very little time to enjoy our cocktails before being rushed to order a bottle of wine with our dinner. Overall, the food was very good, but when we chose to pay a premium and spend our money on a special occasion I would expect better service and treatment.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Excellent service and the staff went out of their way to accommodate us. Thank you!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Delicious food, very good service but very noisy.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Great food and service as always.

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Food and service were top notch, as always!  Consistently the most enjoyable place in town!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Always always outstanding food and service!

Name: Neighborhood Services
Comments: Love the food and service, but too many tables leading to too noisy an atmosphere

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We have tried various "high-end" restaurants in Cincinnati, but none compare to the  Plam Court at the Netherland.  From the elegant environment, personable and knowledgeable wait-staff, to the unparalleled cuisine, one is never disappointed!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wonderful dining experience. From the moment we arrived we were treated as special guests. The food, service and ambiance was all excellent. The room is one of a kind and sets the stage for a wonderful evening. One of Cincinnati‚Äôs very best restaurants.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The service was attentive without being overbearing.   The restaurant is beautiful with a feeling of elegance.   The food was superb.  Overall a very memorable dining experience.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: It was our 25th wedding anniversary and we had a lovely time! The hostess, bread server, and our server, Chris, all wished us happy anniversary, as well as as a card from the restaurant! The food was fun and delicious!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: We've had lunch buffets (Easter, Mothers' Day, etc. at Orchids. They were all very good. Our first opportunity to dine at Orchids was a real experience. Comparing Orchids to the old Maisonette, Boca and Restaurant L (the three legitimate 5-star restaurants we've been to) is a real challenge. Orchids' service staff was above outstanding. Quiet and efficient, the table was cleaned and readied for the next course. The food was wondrous. The seared foie gras, Spanish mackerel, made us want more. The first plates are intentionally small and left us wanting more. Our Monkfish was superbly prepared and surrounded by great food. The chocolate dessert was a wonder. We can't say enough positive about Orchids/ We can also mention that the price was relatively low. Orchids is an unqualified winner.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Service was excellent! Enjoyed our first and second courses immensely, especially bleu cheese beignets and Spanish mackerel. However, we had the monkfish and ribeye entrees and felt that both were lacking and not impressive. Monkfish was dry and seemed overcooked, bouillabaisse was one note and didn‚Äôt hit the mark for us. Ribeye was cooked perfectly and had beautiful presentation, but the flavor was not great, I‚Äôve had much better steaks at chain restaurants.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The Orchids is in a spectacular setting in the historic Netherlands Hotel in downtown Cincinnati. The setting is idea for a relaxing, romantic dinner, or intimate small gathering. Tables are elegant and widely spaced, so very conducive to conversation. No other ambient noise or music. The service is highly attentive and the pacing of the meal was spot on. It was fascinating to watch the choreography of the staff (and the service is clearly choreographed). The staff was friendly, but with a degree of professional aloofness given the more formal dining setting. The prices are expensive although not out of range for the setting. However, the food itself, while well prepared and presented, did not have the distinctive, memorable taste that would befit the prices. I had the ribeye which was well prepared and tasty, but not distinctive. My wife had the flounder which was disappointing in the portion size, taste and accompaniments. We opted to not have dessert, but the restaurant provided some petit fors which were the highlight of the meal. Overall, this is a wonderful place to make an impression and to enjoy a leisurely meal, but is very expensive for the quality and quantity of food. We would recommend, but with caveats.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Morgan, Tate and Oscar are wonderful and made our night fabulous.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food was good, but bland.  The short ribs had a musty smell initially.   The risotto had good flavor except for the celery root.   The blue cheese salad was good.  Service was impressive and everything came out hot.  The restaurant itself is amazing and the Jazz band was a very nice touch.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wonderful dinner with a friend in town for a visit.  Tate was amazing as our server, food and drinks were great, everyone we encountered went above and beyond, and it was a special time.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Incredible food and service.  Can see how they recently received the highest rating.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Chris and his team provided wonderful service!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Absolutely amazing food and service. Staff was knowledgeable and very friendly. I am pescatarian, no meat, and they catered to my diet and gave me a delicious chefs tasting that I will never forget. If you‚Äôre thinking about going, just go. You won‚Äôt regret it.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Great experience.  The food was excellent and complex, but delicious.  My wife and I each ordered four courses, which over the period of 2 hours was just the right amount of food. Service was excellent, and although the menu might be considered haute cuisine, our waiter made us feel very comfortable and at ease.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: The food, service and ambiance are consistently superb.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Wish the meal had been better. Service and ambiance awesome.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: I have consistently had excellent meals here, both at dinner and brunch.  This was an exception.  Service was lackluster, and the food was inconsistently good.  I knew we were in trouble when the bread arrived and was stale.  Overall, this experience did not match the price level.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Fantastic food, service, and hospitality in a beautiful environment.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This is our 2nd time coming here for a special occasion and it was fabulous, just like the first time. The food is exquisite and the service and ambiance couldn't be better!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This is a great restaurant for a special  occasion or just a very good dinner.  The presentation is especially good and the service is excellent.  I highly recommend Orchids.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Food was quite good.  The bouillabaisse was insultingly modest (filled with potatoes and little seafood [no monkfish as advertised].  For $48, you HAVE to do better!Service was very spotty.  Busing of the table barely occurred.  For a five star restaurant?Seemed like there was no one managing or guiding a VERY young staff.  Simply not impressive.Go to Restaurant L or Jeff Ruby to see how fine dining is done.Music was fantastic.  Ambience?  Fantastic.  Good waiter that had little support.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Everything was great!!  The food was perfection and service wonderful!!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: Food and service were outstandingin every way, but the noise from the nearby bar was a little high for our taste. When dining at a restaurant of the quality and price point, a quieter atmosphere would be appreciated.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This has become an annual tradition for my wife's birthday.  Each year we continue to be impressed with the knowledge and attentiveness of the wait staff.  The food is always excellent and the ambiance unmatched.  Many thanks to Orchids for a memorable night on a special occasion!

Name: Orchids at Palm Court
Comments: This was my second time dining at Orchids at Palm Court.  The first time I dined here was last year and it was fantastic.  This year was a different story.  To start off, it should be noted that this is a relatively expensive restaurant and therefore comes with certain expectations beyond food, service and ambiance being two of them.  We were seated by a very friendly, knowledgeable, and professional greeter, Morgan.  Our server, Oscar, was also very professional.  However, it took 40 minutes from the time we were seated to meet Oscar.  He was extremely busy and for a Saturday night Orchids was poorly staffed--labor cuts?  In any event, we were looking forward to the actual meal.  My wife ordered the blue cheese beignet salad, popcorn grits, and scallops.  I ordered the beef cheek perogies, maitake/cappelletti, and lamb.  My wife's salad was very overdressed and almost seemed as if there was too much salad dressing on it, then the chefs decided to pour olive oil on it--what a disappointment.  The popcorn grits, on the other hand, were flavorful and delicious and I would definitely recommend this unique and tasty dish!  And my wife's third course of scallops were cooked perfectly.  My order was a different story.  First, my perogies had absolutely no flavor whatsoever-no salt, pepper, herb, or sauce-and therefore was unsurprisingly very bland.  The maitake and cappelletti were terrific and cooked perfectly, and the sauce was a perfect pairing (you should order this).  But sadly, my entr√©e was lackluster.  The lamb was almost rare and had, once again, no flavor.  The entr√©e did come with two bites of lamb sausage and creamy polenta, but the what should have been the star of the plate, the protein, disappointed in flavor and the way it was cooked.Along with service being painfully slow, the staff always seemed rushed and in a hurry to leave the table.  The staff was so hurried that for our second course they gave my wife and me the wrong second course.  Loud patrons.

Name: Orchids at Palm Court

The space was elegant and comfortable and we scarcely noticed anyone else. Oriole equals Alinea in quality but is a very different experience, not theatrical, not startling, but full of pleasing surprises. I hope to find an excuse (and the means) to return ‚Äì we're truly fortunate to have such a restaurant in Chicago.

She indicated that due to the pandemic there was limited seating availability.  As we sat and observed the patrons around (most of whom were in full or partial shade) we realized that they were seating parties of 2 at the tables for 4 which were in the shade.  Due to the excessive heat and relentless sun, the usually lovely experience was a bit of a nightmare. We feel that this was an easily remedied situation that was ignored, and this visit was unfortunate.

Homeless come by and either beg for food/money or play instruments, and management does not step in while you are having dinner.  This restaurant is right of the park, yes.  But you can't treat people bad just because of your location and charge the prices that you do for mediocre food.  Complete disappointment, won't be returning.

It was supposed to be an anniversary lunch and we had high expectations that usually get met at Parc. This time was different. Our waiter took forever to even start bringing water. The bread came before we had utensils and my drink came after we got our starter, which also took forever but was delicious I might add. Then another 30 min 'til my pepper-steak arrived, which was inedible. I hardly was able to get the VERY sharp knife through the meat and they offered to replace it. Considering all the wait-time and frustration I agreed to take it home and they actually offered to take it off the bill, which we refused. We will of course go back but it was not exactly a desirable event.

No apology, but rather an excuse that the wine was ‚Äúprobably married with something else‚Äù(!) was given. Seriously. The waiter was a touch smug and casual bordering on unprofessional. A thousand dollar meal needs to be perfect. This was not. We have eaten at other 3 Michelin star restaurants and this one didn‚Äôt hold up.

Since our last visit the bar area within Per Se has been turned into tables for dining so they have increased their covers.When we did get in we still had to wait for our table and so sat at a high bar area. The tasting menu was great with a lot of choice and standard of the food was excellent again so we weren't disappointed. The staff were very professional and happy to chat - getting the balance on this is quite difficult in my opinion and after a rocky start  they certainly succeeded.This is a very special restaurant and although expensive a place for celebrations.

Name: Per Se
Comments: It was excellent from start to finish.

Name: Per Se
Comments: Just ‚ÄòFabulous ‚Äò in every way! A huge treat and well worth it!

Name: Per Se
Comments: For me this is ‚Äúdestination‚Äù dinning. I go to NY  often and it‚Äôs nice to experience the top restaurants once in a while. This was semi short notice so the only time available was for Lunch on Saturday. Everything about the restaurant was super outstanding, especially the service, which is becoming rated these days. Unfortunately we were next to a table, they‚Äôre not that close, of four that included a 12-13 year old boy. It‚Äôs not that children are bad, it‚Äôs the failed parenting strategies that have forgotten about the seldom seen and never heard theories of children in upscale public places. I wish they would have a grown up only policy.

Name: Per Se
Comments: This is a dining establishment beyond compare. Prepare to be pampered while you take in view of the NY skyline and relax in the glow of the fireplace. All waiters are graduates of a culinary school who will help you create the dining experience of a lifetime. 12 plates and an assortment of desserts are served to order at your leisure. The cuisine is original, and diverse with flavors that coax and tease the taste buds. The quality of ingredients is unrivaled; so much so that "Bread and Butter" is an entree - "A smoked Paprika 'Parker House Roll' served with Diane St Clair's Animal Farm Butter." Diane has 10 cows that she milks and hand churns the butter. No detail is left to chance. All chairs that are not required are removed from the table (before you arrive) so as not to disturb the intimacy. There are as many servers as there are guests who move stealthily to present your next palate-stimulating tasting.No matter your requirements (allergies, vegan, etc) Chef Keller and his staff will ensure that you literally have the meal of a lifetime.

Name: Per Se
Comments: We had easily one of the best meals we have ever had at Per Se.  The tasting menu was incredibly well put together.  Each course seemed to improve upon the one before it.  The service was even better, with very attentive (but unintrusive) staff who took care to explain the dishes and get to know us throughout the dinner.  The pace was prompt, without being rushed and worked through the menu in just about two hours.  Capped off our experience with a kitchen tour and personal compliments to the chefs. Can‚Äôt recommend Per Se enough!

Name: Per Se
Comments: Amazing! There are Michelin restaurants and then there is a Per Se.

Name: Per Se

Comments: Quince lives up to its reputation.  Expensive?  Yes.  Worth the price?  I have to say Yes, again.  We went in the middle of the week, so not crowded.  Service was wonderful.  At first, I was concerned that there were too many different servers and wine masters attending to us.  But each had a specialty, and a story to tell.  Juan, in particular, provided insight to and history behind the cutlery and china.  Robert paced us through and described each course expertly.  And the food--well, there was nothing that was not perfect.  Oysters in a cream and nettle sauce.  White asparagus prepared two ways.  Wagyu beef--both American and Japanese bred.  Additional treats besides what is listed on the day's menu.  By the time we arrived at the beautiful dessert trolly, I could hardly eat another thing.  Definitely take your time.  We were there for well over 4 hours, and enjoyed every minute.

Started annoyed with 6 texts, 2 phone calls, and 1 e-mail asking me to confirm reservation.  Each one answered.  Over-hyped place - won't go back

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Partner enjoyed the food, then the bar with quite great  characters and conversation which made the night complete.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fantastic as usual!  Raouls consistently delivers an amazing food and ambiance experience.  I‚Äôd recommend it to anyone and everyone!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Ever mouthful was perfection!! Love this place it‚Äôs So consistent for great food quality and service!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: This cozy but very loud restaurant is home to perhaps the most outstanding Steak au Poivre I have ever had. The cut of meat was excellent, cooked to a perfect medium and crusted in just the right amount and consistency of pepper... served with a perfectly seasoned sauce of exactly the right consistency... and of course accompanied by a basket of crispy Frites! It doesn‚Äôt get much better than this! Exactly what I would expect from an Alsace heritage which, arguably produces the best chefs in all of Europe!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Food was delicious, overall great experience

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Food and cocktails were fantastic.  Steak au Poivre was amazing.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: This was an amazing find on this past trip. It had an old school feel given all its history in the city. My son LOVED the burger. This is a kid who doesn‚Äôt like sauce or much adornment on his burgers so the meat has to be spot on - this burger didn‚Äôt disappoint AND the pepper sauce was so good, he ATE ALL OF IT!!  All the food was divine and definitely a staple for our yearly visits toNYC from now on!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: One of my NYC favorites!!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Loved everything

Name: Raoul's
Comments: The food and lively atmosphere is always fantastic!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great evening to enjoy my nieces birthday!

Name: Raoul's

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Always a great time at this legendary place

Name: Raoul's
Comments: My favorite place in the city!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fabulous burger -- worth the hype! The fries were also a pleasant surprise too.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Overpriced but not remarkable.  The waitstaff was curt. I would not go back.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Exceptional service and food at this well known restaurant. Really enjoyed our evening.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Good food, Poor service; table not ready, then after being directed to the bar were told we couldn‚Äôt transfer the bar bill to our table. Waiter was slow and inattentive, didn‚Äôt provide plates for the bread, didn‚Äôt once check in on the food, had to be asked three times for a drinks refill and provided dessert menus but didn‚Äôt come to take an order for 15 minutes....

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great service and food! If you note a birthday celebration in open table they remember and add a candle to your desert which is great.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Fantastic night at this iconic new york restaurant.  The steak au poivre was perfectly cooked and delicious.  The choice of sides was great and the grilled broccoli was really tasty.  A huge wine list was also good with a massive selection of french as well as us wines.  Would definitely go again next time in NYC.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great service. Nice wine menu. Delicious food. A true neighborhood gem. Can‚Äôt wait to go back again.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: YOU WILL BE CHARGED $100 to cancel reservations. Still a great place!!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Wonderful old school French brassiere with classic French cuisine done extremely well.  From the steak au pouvrie to the pomme  frites to the profiteroles you can‚Äôt go wrong.  Excellent service, as well.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Sexy crowd and the best steak au poivre in town. My go-to spot for a fun night out.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: 80th Birthday

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Beautiful space with interesting artwork. The food and wine were great and the ambiance was lovely. Service was the best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Raoul's will always be our favorite place. The staff and food (especially the burger) are the absolute best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great burgers. My neighborhood favorite!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: I LOVE RAOUL'S!  My husband and I meet for late dinners here and always roll home full, tipsy and elated.  The service is really always outstanding.  Everything from the bar/ host staff's greeting to the experience at the table makes us feel so well cared for; I find the interpersonal style of the team to be very direct, professional, and effective, but also always warm.  This place is such a New York institution; it's an absolute privilege to enjoy it from time to time.  Thanks to the whole damn team!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Wonderful meal from beginning to end

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Never disappoints!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Amazing classic French style restaurant.The food is exquisite and the atmosphere fantastic. It‚Äôs not for those looking for a quiet night out as noise levels are high but I wouldn‚Äôt have it any other way. Efficient staff, eclectic artwork and food so delicious that my mouth waters at the mere thought of it! Go!! It should be illegal not to!

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Raoul‚Äôs is the best. It‚Äôs our regular go-to because while the food is really great (get the frisbee salad no matter what else you do)- the people are incredible and make you feel so welcome and at home. Plenty of celebrities come to this old school restaurant that has stayed popular for over 40 years but they treat  everyone wonderfully and care more how you behave than who you are

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Best steak au poivre ever, great Cosmo, fab music, cool scene. I will definitely return. Sometimes I look so hard for something new.... so glad I chose a classic to celebrate my husband‚Äôs 50th.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Tremendous spot.  A+ food, service. Traditional and current. Love it. Rivals the best.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: Great food, ambiance, service.  Hands down our favorite restaurant in NYC.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: One of the best burgers in town.

Name: Raoul's
Comments: The food is great and good value. I like the ambiance a lot. Dark with a European feel. Waitstaff are all competent but there are big inconsistencies in servers.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent meal & service. Best Indian food I've ever had.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Very tasty, though there are other trendy, high end restaurants where I do feel like you get more bang for your buck than here.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent in every way. Amazing food, service, room, noise level. Only knock for me personally was dessert, but that is more my tastes than their execution.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great modern take on Indian food.  Looking forward to my next visit.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Once again, we all had great meals and great service. Rasika is the best indian food in town.

Name: Rasika
Comments: The food is delicious. I would recommend the restaurant to others.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Nice place. Good food. Always on our list for when we are in the mood for Indian food.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Outstanding food and service each time I visited.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Exceptional food and service!Outstanding experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Creative food, great vibe and service. Liked trying Indian beer.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Nice restaurant, food was good, not great. Didn‚Äôt understand what all the hype is about, but will give it another shot in the future.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Never been disappointed. Just fantastic Indian food with a modern flair.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Amazing delicious food! Great fun for a night of fine dining!

Name: Rasika
Comments: The food here is amazing.  Particularly the fish dishes (cod and bass).  I would eat it daily if I could.

Name: Rasika
Comments: A must-try if you love Indian food when you're in DC.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Dining at Rasika is an every-year holiday event. The service, ambiance, and food are spectacular. I always order the black cod and I'm never disappointed.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Fabulous food- and I mean everything we've ever eaten here.Great service and the decor!!

Name: Rasika
Comments: Absolutely delicious food!  Great service and lovely ambiance. A DC must!!

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent service and amazing food. Consistent great quality.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Delicious food options, albeit pricey. Nice for a date

Name: Rasika
Comments: Rasika is by far one of the best Indian restaurants in the DC region.  You will not be disappointed.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Best Indian restaurant in the dc area.  Sometimes hard to get in so reserve well ahead.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Hands down the best Indian food I've ever had.  Never fails to impress.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Alway a great place to eat -- you cannot go wrong.

Name: Rasika
Comments: This is one of the best Indian restaurants in all my experiences with Indian restaurants.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Loved the everything on the tasting menu. Nice ambiance.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great tapas sized servings good for sharing a lot of dishes

Name: Rasika
Comments: I loved the Palaak Chaat. Food was great. Would recommend for a slow dining experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: I love this restaurant. The flavors are bold and delicious. The service is outstanding every time I go ( I have been to Rasika 3 times now). I highly recommend this restaurant for lunch or dinner in DC (either location is great).

Name: Rasika
Comments: Service was great, food was good but portions were so small and none of the dishes come with rice... you need to order rice and pay for it.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Food was mildly spiced and excellent.  They handled a large party of 20 or so very well.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Many good dishes; however, my experience here, with its modest portion sizes and sometimes too subtle flavors, left me missing the experience I get at a good, traditional, American-Indian buffet.

Name: Rasika
Comments: This is my favorite Indian restaurant. Love, love, love.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Good. Hidden gem. Food was good and so was service. Beautiful place. Not expected.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Delicious! Great service and ambiance. Would recommend for a special evening out.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent, unique, Indian food and lovely ambiance.

Name: Rasika
Comments: A little pricey but the food and service are consistently fantastic

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great meal! Tried the tasting menu so explored many dishes.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Excellent food and service.  An authentic dining experience.

Name: Rasika
Comments: Great ambiance, food selection, and variety. Great service by wait staff and managers. Attentive but not helicopter-ish. Great for intimate groups (4-8).

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a fabulous experience. From the moment we're greeted at the door we feel like royalty visiting somewhere else. What an atmosphere in the dining room. Expert wait staff, and the absolute finest food in Cincinnati - and that's a high bar given the alternatives available. Go with the the 3 (or 2) course menu and wine pairings for an unbelievable taste experience.  Not something we can afford very frequently but we get there for the big events.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Excellent food and service. Duck and lamb were excellent!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Always great. The Rabbit is phenomenal. Service and ambiance can't be beat.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Jean-Robert defines elegant dining in his several venues across town. Restaurant's impeccable service is utterly unobtrusive and the servers are well-informed. We have dined there on several occasions, both in the restaurant and in the bar, and have come away pleased. This time we opted for the 2-course dinner with pairings, and while the food itself was well-prepared it was not the perfection we had come to known. The wine pairings, though, were superb, as were the selection of in-house pastries for dessert.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Great slow dining experience to appreciate delicious food and wine.  For those that appreciate fine dining, classy atmosphere and are willing to pay for it.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Wonderful! Menu gourmand was exceptional ! Decor and ambience perfection. Can not say enough good things. A must

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Best restaurant in Cincinnati with beautiful ambiance, diverse menu beautifully presented food offering good value ( bargain compared to large cities) impeccable service,  No one does fine dining better than owners Richard Brown & Jean Rober

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: An awesome menu. Perfect setting. Brilliant presentation. Great tasting dinner. Fabulous wait staff. And...all of that plus Jean Robert de Cavel in the kitchen. I could not ask for more, but I did...all of this in a very friendly. "non-stuffy" atmosphere. PERFECT!Put this winner on your restaurant "bucket list" for sure!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Simply the most elegant restaurant in Cincinnati.  Best food between New York and Chicago.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Amazing food!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was wonderful from staff to food. Nice ambiance.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: L has an attention to detail that is unmatched in the tri-state area.  Outside of NYC, there are few places that I've seen that can execute to this level of perfection.  Every detail of the dinning experience, from the grand bar and service, to the entry of the magnificent dinning room, to dinning service - all done with grace and flawless delivery.  No detail in the dinning experience is trivialized.  The thoughtfulness is seen throughout a perfectly choreographed experience.  Their attention to GF was outstanding.  I'm grateful to have this set of amazing restaurateurs in Cincinnati that can have this level of execution.Thank you, team L for another wonderful experience.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Having had superb dining experiences in the past, there is not much more to say except it is still superb. Service, food, and ambiance continue to be in the top tier in Cincinnati. For a very special evening at, by the quality standard of the restaurant, a very reasonable price, one could not find a better place to dine.We will go back often.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was delightful....music agreeable, but a tad too loud...

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Restaurant L is a very special destination and we had a wonderful evening!  Be prepared to spend time there, enjoy the atmosphere and excellent service, as well as the exquisite cuisine.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: An experience! The ambiance is outstanding and the food is delicious. Service and taste were at a level I've never experienced before.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Just a wonderful experience. This is why it is one of the very best restaurants in Cincinnati. Expensive but worth it. Service was great!!!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Wow!  Tremendous service and food!  The chef was amazing and greeted our group a couple times to explain the menu.  He was fantastic!!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: L is my wife's favorite " special occasion" restaurant.   The gourmand menu was superb as well as the service.  Thank you Max and Richard.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: This is our favorite restaurant for special occasions.  It was great to see chef greeting guests.  Everything was superb and outstanding.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: First time there, met a friend for lunch.Was offered the Friday express lunch in the lounge so we decided on that. First course was soup or salad and second course was a Pho burger or chicken crepes for $12.Delicious!! Will go back again for dinner.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a gem in red neck Cincinnati, the place is somptuous, the service perfect although a bit too fast, they wanted to close early, with just three tables that evening. The show is the inventive food of the French chef, at the level of a  star Michelin if the inspectors knew where Cincinnati was! A bemol to this otherwise perfect evening: the wine pairing done with perfectly low quality boring wines. Not acceptable for such gorgeous food.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Love the restaurant.  When I want a casual night out with friends, I go to the bar area.  Couldn't be better.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: A wonderful experience from start to finish!

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was delicious. Ambience was great and the staff was fantastic.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Everything was perfect, as expected.  One table of six got a little loud periodically.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Exactly what should come with fine French dining....great cuisine, great wine, attentive and gracious service.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Outstanding preparation and service.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Every visit to Restaurant L is a wonderful experience. The food, service and staff make this a visit to be enjoyed and savored. The presentation is wonderful and the food is excellent. Love the wine pairing option. This enhances the flavor of each course. The room is beautiful and the ambiance special.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: AAAAMMMMMAAAZZZZIINNGG!   It was a perfect date night the food was fabulous!  The staff was great and informative!  We had the Gourmand menu and it‚Äôs was wonderful from start to finish.  The dining room ambiance was great

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: The service was exceptional as usual. Only one error, a colleague asked for more bread which never came. Food was amazing.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: This was a wonderful dining experience ! The food was excellent and the service was outstanding !

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: We each got the 3 course Prix Fixe menu. What a great way to try multiple delicious food.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Beautiful and delicious, a great experience

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: What a great choice to celebrate my wife's birthday.  We have always enjoyed the Orchids but it has not met our expectations in  quality of food and service.  We decided to try Restaurant L this year and were pleasantly surprised.  There were many mixed reviews regarding L, but nothing but raves from us.  The room was beautiful and the service was superb.  The food and presentation outstanding.  We chose the three course dinner with the wine pairings  WOW for both. The flavors of each course were wonderful and the venison hit the jackpot.  The wines worked very well with the food and certainly enhanced the flavors of the evening.  We certainly look forward to return visits.  In our book it is the best restaurant in Cincinnati.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: 3 course prix fixe with wine pairing. 5 star Euro experience from start to finish Chef came to  each table to greet and check in. Staff knowledgeable and very open and personable. Richard Brown is wonderful historian of restaurant industry in Cincinnati as well as NYC and Europe.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: Nothing can beat their Friday express linch in the bar.  2 courses for $12.  Of course we included a bottle of wine and desserts too.  The soups here are always heavenly and no one does salmon like this place.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: We went to L's to celebrate my sister-in-law's retirement.  We had great quiet evening where the staff continued to excel in everything they did.  The drinks were outstanding and the menu was better than expected.  I'm looking forward to my next visit to L's, to see what's new on the menu.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: While we enjoyed the relaxed atmosphere and felt no rush, some of the service did lag a bit.  However, we were greatly accommodated and we are happy to recommend Restaurant L to others.

Name: Restaurant L
Comments: My wife and I had a wonderful Christmas lunch. The 4 course tasting menu was superb! Always a wonderful time at L. It is a very special place.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The food is delightful and the service is impeccable.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Amazing food and amazing service still one of the best in Chicago.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Riccardo never disappoints. Enoteca is my favorite location, but my experience at all three locations have been consistently exceptional. The food is truly outstanding, and the service impeccable. Everyone‚Äîfrom the servers, support staff, and management‚Äîis personable, friendly, and happy to see you. I highly recommend our server, JP. He is conversational, funny, and delivers excellent service. I have a hard time not ordering my favorite dish: Rigatoni alla Buttera. This time, we also tried the burrata over arugula with pesto and the tortelloni. Both wonderful. As a restaurant manager, I am not ashamed to say this is my favorite restaurant in the city, and I do not work here!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great to be back on the patio! Food as good as ever!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The staff is always friendly, accomodating and safe.  JP and Juan are always quick to remember you and help cover each others table if need be.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: What a great night! The outdoor tables on the sidewalk were shaded and attractive, the service was friendly and attentive and the food was great.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent! Great neighborhood spot - we will be back!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Wonderful service, great patio. Will definitely be back!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Dinner outside with two friends, service was top notch with very attendance waiter and food/ wine was fantastic ! We were part of the uncovered patio and when it started raining our server moved us under the umbrella with all new silverware, which was greatly appreciated. Highly recommend this spot for great Italian, nice portions and a wonderful ambiance !

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Absolutely fantastic!   Sat outside and we were covered by the passing rain shower.   The food was delicious and service top notch.   So happy we found this restaurant!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: We had a 9 p.m. reservation Friday evening and it was so nice to be able to dine at Riccardo Enoteca again! We felt the table distancing and precautions were excellent. The service and food were exceptional, as usual!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Amazing experience overall! Fantastic service and fantastic experience.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Old reliable. The most consistently good restaurant in Chicago.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: They have a decent wine collection. Good service too.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The service was amazing. The entire staff was extremely friendly and attentive. The food was delicious. Loved it and will definitely return.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is a very cozy neighborhood restaurant that has a terrific menu to please a variety of tastes. The help is exceptional--friendly, helpful and efficient. I have dined here many times and will continue to do so! It is a bit pricey but worth the $$ since the dishes are so delicious.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Perfect neighborhood spot worth leaving your own neighborhood to visit! Delicious food, great ambience, professional and friendly service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Very accommodating, will custom prepare a dish if necessary.  Authentic cooking and great neighborhood atmosphere .

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Best Italian restaurant in the city!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Everything was so good; the wine, the complementary bruschetta, arugula salad, prosciutto pizza, and surprise birthday tiramisu. Friend was late for our reservation, no problem. We  shared a pizza, no judgement. Very friendly, genuine service -  attentive and unobtrusive. Genuine Italian fresh, quality food full of flavor- the cooks have the gift! Welcoming, soothing, and lively atmosphere. A real gem. Highly recommended.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Lovely spot with so many great food choices it was hard to pick!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent everything! Would recommend for any event or just dinner. Value is excellent, great wine selection and the food was best I‚Äôve had since leaving NJ. Will definitely be back.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Always such a great meal and outstanding service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Always love Riccardo's.  Friendly staff and delicious food.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Absolutely love this place. Classic italian, delicious food, low key setting.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: I am always amazed at the quality of the food and the excellence of the service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is one of our favorite restaurants of all time.  We live a five minute walk away and always ask ourselves why we don't eat here more often.  The service is helpful and friendly.  The food is outstanding.  Never had a bad time here.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food is wonderful and the service was exceptional. Made us feel special.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Excellent neighborhood restaurant. Exceptional food and super personable and professional staff.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food and service were excellent. We came on a VERY cold night and were seated just in front of the door and asked if we'd be frozen out in that location. We were offered a 20-30 minute wait for another table but they said we'd be OK. The restaurant has a long entry between the outside door and the inside door. There is a sign asking people to make sure that the outside door is closed before opening the inside door. A member of the restaurant staff spent much of his time by the inside door to make sure that guests observed the request.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Great pizza, good wine selection and friendly neighborhood spot.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: This is one of my favorite restaurants in Lincoln Park. Cesar, JP, Juan and all of the chefs and staff are top notch ‚Äî friendly, courteous and always provide great recommendations, superior service and delicious meals. I cannot say enough about how much we adore Cesar! Riccardo should be very proud of him and all who make this restaurant so great! And Riccardo himself is the best of the best of all chefs in Chicago and a lovely, kind, intelligent, amazing person too! I do not know many who have his passion, kind heart and amazing talent!!!

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Food and ambiance was of the highest quality.  Highly recommend this place.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: A neighborhood gem. We come often for the authentic food and excellent service. I‚Äôm from New York City; the size and vibe remind me of home.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Wonderful and quiet New Year‚Äôs Eve dinner. Simply delicious.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Best small venue Italian in Chicago!!!  The food is always great and the service is even better.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: Birthday celebration. Great place to enjoy w friends. Great food and service.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: We love Riccardo Enoteca. Really really love it. Special occasion, every day. We always have a reason to go.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: One of a few restaurants open on Christmas Eve, we had a great meal here.  The Milanese style pizza was revelatory with its crisp, light crust.  The lasagna and the lobster fettuccine were fantastic, as were the scallops.  Excellent wine list, too.

Name: Riccardo Enoteca
Comments: The food is always delicious and inventive. And the staff, charming. Our favorite neighborhood spot.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Fantastic restaurant with innovative food.  Packed every night.  Tip - go and wait at 5.30pm when they just open and you can sit at the bar!

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Incredible food, incredible service. Would go back in a heartbeat but very difficult to get a reservation.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Another amazing place....excellent food and experience.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Always a solid choice.  Creative menu, smart wait staff.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Absolutely loved the place.  Our waiter was very nice and helped us make good menu selections for it being our first time visiting.

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Top notch culinary experience, yet you may come away hungry

Name: Rich Table
Comments: Fabulous.  Great for foodies, anniversaries, theatre.  Just great food and wine

Name: Rich Table

She also brought us a variety of readers when our waitress only brought one pair that were too strong for someone that needed it so I appreciated her so much because I would not have been happy with our experience at all if it wasn't for her. You could tell she cared about our experience which I really appreciated. Also there was a misunderstanding with our waitress on the salads and who was splitting what so we had to order another salad because the way it was split up (which I appreciated that they split them for us), there was a person that was left out and was not brought out a salad. Other than that, the food was outstanding but maybe it was just a bad night but I think service needs to be taken up a notch because that is also a very important part of the dining experience.

Comments: We have been going to Rudy and Pacos for 20 plus years and have always enjoyed it in the past. This time the food was just ok.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: Great food and service.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: As we walked into Rudy and Paco, i immediately knew that the restaurant  exceeded my expectations. The upscale, but comfortable and almost historical feel of the place assured us that we made a good choice. Our experience only got better from there. We were greeted my Paco himself before we were taken to our table by a very friendly hostess. Shortly thereafter our waitress introduced herself and brought us a lovely plate of ribboned plantains with chimichurri sauce and ‚ÄúPaco Pico‚Äù sauce. The light and crunchy plantains successfully served to whet our appetite for the rest of our highly-anticipated meal. My husband and I shared a plate of escargot. The delightfully soft and warm bread that accompanied the dish was quite pleasing. As we were there to celebrate our anniversary, we ordered a Prosecco cocktail that was enhanced by hibiscus syrup with candied Hibiscus at the bottom of our glasses. It was a great Segway into our main course. My favorite thing about Galveston seafood restaurants is that they know how to prepare gulf coast seafood- Rudy and Paco‚Äôs treatment of the red snapper that I ordered was painstakingly good! It was cooked to perfection and adorned (not overdressed) by avocado, Paco Pico, and lump crab meat...good stuff!  My husband wasn‚Äôt too fond of the scallops dish he ordered stating that they were ‚Äúcold and not very flavorful.‚Äù Aside from that, the wine selection was ample, and my tres leches dessert was heavenly! It was swimming in the milks that flavored each drenched and spongy bite! My only critique, if I have to list one, is that the sides are lacking. Although I am a purist, and I like my veggies plain and lightly steamed which they executed successfully, I feel that a restaurant of their caliber should step up their sides game. I loved the brocolini, but I would have appreciated a wider range of sides from which to choose such as a lively beet salad to compliment that beautiful piece of fish. I would, and will definitely return!

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar
Comments: What a great experience! I spilled some of the sauce on my dress shirt and Paco was over in an instant with club soda to wash it out.  He is attentive and a great restauranteur.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar

The attention to detail and unique, delectable dishes paired with an upscale, elegant atmosphere makes Rudy & Paco‚Äôs one of the most absolutely delightful places to dine anywhere.

Name: Rudy & Paco Restaurant & Bar

Food was amazing as always. Loved seeing Casey back and visiting w Elvis. Shinsei will always be one of my top three go-to places.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air

There is a free valet but the parking can be a mess. Part of a decent set of restaurants halfway between west side and the valley.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air
Comments: Consistently great fish and always wonderful, warm service. A classic spot.

Name: SHU - Sushi House Unico - Bel Air

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Hillary‚Äôs knowledge of the menu and ab Uluru to pair your likes perfectly with the menu is amazing. Thanks for going above and beyond with the crostatas, be back soon!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Excellent experience as always. Social distancing and very well trained staff made the difference. We love Sotto, but miss a few items from the old menu. A menu refresh would be welcomed.

Name: Sotto
Comments: We celebrated our engagement at Sotto and it was nothing short of absolutely wonderful! We had a great dinner with excellent service and knowledgeable employees who elevated our experience as they explained more about the reasoning behind wine and menu items. Didn't disappoint, as usual!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Sotto is a Cincinnati treasure. This is our most favorite place, we come here to celebrate the things that matter in our life.We have also come ‚Äújust because‚Äù, and we have never been let down. Everything about the place is first class - food, wine and staff.We had been waiting anxiously to get back, and plan to return again soon(before anything else happens)!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Amazing food & service every single time!!!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Justin is a great waiter! Took really good care of us! Had a super Tuscan bottle of wine. Yummy! The branzino delish & the cappellacci excellent! Have never had a bad meal. I drive in from Detroit every 3 months and make it point to eat there every time. ‚ù§Ô∏è

Name: Sotto
Comments: We'd heard great things about this place so, when we came into town (from Chicago), we got a chance to try it ourselves and found it excellent. Great food, beautiful ambiance and top rate service. The prices were very reasonable as well. We had appetizers, entrees and desserts with drinks for a family of three for under a hundred bucks. And for this level of restaurant it's hard to find that. We'll definitely be back whenever we're in town.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Outstanding service and food was excellent!

Name: Sotto
Comments: 3 words - order the octopus.  If you've never had it, or just thought "eww", then you are missing out.  Have a couple drinks (a new favorite of mine is the "murder hornet"), get past the "eww" and try it.  It isn't what you think, and it is absolutely delicious and tender.   If you've had it, then you know what I'm talking about.  As far as the rest of the food goes, I've never had anything there I didn't like.  A recent stand-out was the spring pea tortellini.  I think I could just sit and eat several bowls of that, and nothing else, it was so good.  The quail is delicious, as is the branzino, and the short rib.  In fact it's all good, and the pastas are outstanding.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Excellent. Great service and amazing food!

Name: Sotto
Comments: This is our anniversary dinner every year. In my opinion, Sotto‚Äôs always has been and continues to be the most knowledgeable staff of any restaurant that I have ever been. Even in the current environment (COVID), the staff remained warm and welcoming, and multiple team members stopped and wished us a happy anniversary. I write a glowing review every year, and each year it is well deserved.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Great COVID dining experience! Super friendly staff, all wearing masks, mindful of health restrictions while delivering the Sotto quality service and delicious dining experience. Our lovely server brought out a chocolate dessert with a candle at the end of our meal. The music was a bit loud but there were fewer people in the restaurant to absorb the sound. I would highly recommend SOTTO! Go eat there.  Let's keep them in business.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Everything about our dinner was wonderful our server Robert was outstanding.

Name: Sotto
Comments: One of the best restaurants in the city top to bottom.

Name: Sotto
Comments: My wife and I chose Sotto to celebrate our 4th wedding anniversary.  Our experience from start to finish was top notch.  We started with the goat cheese and hazelnut honey bread, which was outstanding.  We then had the asparagus pasta and black kale salad as an appetizer, both were equally delicious.  Our entrees consisted of the breaded pork loin and short rib ravioli.  The breaded pork loin was the best pork I‚Äôve ever had, the crisp was absolutely perfect, and the lemon butter sauce mouth-watering.  The short rib ravioli was soft and decadent.  We then finished off with the ricotta doughnuts, which were a great ending to the night. Our server, Mark,  was very knowledgeable and passionate about the food and explaining the menu.  He took great care of us the entire night, as well as the supporting staff.  We will certainly be back!

Name: Sotto
Comments: Food was delicious!  Recommend Cucumber Blossom cocktail

Name: Sotto
Comments: The service here was amazing. Our first time here, Robert went through the whole menu and gave us recommendations on food and wine. The food was phenomenal. Want to go back tonight. Short rib pasta was out of this world, as were the ricotta doughnuts.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Perfect on all account as expected. We will be back.

Name: Sotto
Comments: The food portions are small, the menu options were limited and the quality of the food doesn't reflect the high price tag.  I don't see a reason to come back here ever again

Name: Sotto
Comments: It‚Äôs was amazing

Name: Sotto
Comments: Brian did a fantastic job taking care of us. He was knowledgeable and attentive to our needs. The staff that assisted in bringing out the various courses did well.

Name: Sotto
Comments: Service was great as always!  Read the table well, we enjoyed the personality.  Brazino was amazing!  As was the Tortolini

Name: Sotto
Comments: It was absolutely incredible as always!!! We love everything about Sotto!!!

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto
Comments: Phenomenal service and quality‚Äîlive the local produce!

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto

Name: Sotto
