Name: Spinasse
Comments: Charming restaurant with Piedmontese wines, condensed menu with well-executed and delicious food, as well as warm friendly and sincere service.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: The family style meal was a fantastic way to spend an evening with friends. The staff was also attentive and friendly. Will definitely do  again... and again.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: It was for my bf‚Äôs birthday. The food was so amazing that we were both blown away. Def a good choice for any type of celebration.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: excellent, as always!

Name: Spinasse

It was more food than we could finish but we took everything extra to go so we could enjoy the amazing leftovers the next day. Ambiance was cozy, service was superb and the wine paired perfectly with the food. Highly recommend!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Amazing! Some of the best service I've had, ever! Beautiful romantic ambience, amazing food, great wine selection. Highly recommend this spot :)

Name: Spinasse
Comments: The tasting menu was an outstanding choice for our table of four.  We got to indulge in all of the offerings family style and were not disappointed by the variety and flavors.  The amber negroni cocktail and barolo red wine were memorable as well!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: This was our second time dining at Spinasse and it did not disappoint. The pastas were as delicate and delicious as we remember. The service is always top notch and they really went above and beyond this time. The first time we dined, there was a bit of a mix-up with our credit card but it really was no big deal to us. Spinasse provided us with a free appetizer during our dining experience this time which really showed their genuine care for their customers and patrons. By the way, the complimentary poached egg appetizer was AMAZING.All in all, a delicious meal and definitely reinforced our decision to keep coming back!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Thank you for the best meal yet - complete with wonderfully kind service. Always feels like home.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great ambience, food, and service. The pasta is amazing. Excellent wine selection but a little pricey. It can be noisy.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: We have had dinner at Spinasse 4 or 5 times now and we love it every time. Incredible food that is different from your normal/typical Italian food. They feature "Piedmont" style Italian and it is unlike any other restaurant with top quality. Simple recipes that are executed to perfection.When you go, you MUST have the butter sage pasta. It is worth the trip by itself!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Our server was attentive and courteous. Food was excellent! Will definitely come back.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great food, great service and ambiance. Never disappoints!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Stunningly good pasta.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great Piedmont cuisine and wine. Be treated by staff that knows the menu and cares.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: My first time here.  Very impressed.  One of the best restaurants in Seattle.  Inventive menu, great atmosphere and good value.  Definitely will be back.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Food was amazing and service perfect. A little disappointed that hot tea was not available, but hostess was happy to provide hot water to sip after a full meal. Honestly, some of the best Italian pasta on the west coast.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: There are many Italian restaurants in Seattle and I have eaten at many of them, but Spinass's agnolotti (the evening's special) were squisito...tiny, tasty and just plain perfect!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Very good place for a intimate experience, good food and ambience. I recommend their antipasti sampler and the porkchops.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As always, an excellent meal and service.  Thank you for making our friend's birthday special.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: As good as always. Great food, service and wine. One of our go to spots in Seattle.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Lovely atmosphere and fantastic linguine. Would venture to say the best Tiramisu that I've come across. Will most definitely be back as soon as possible!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Spinasse is by far the best restaurant in Seattle. The food is phenomenal and the service is unmatched. Love coming here!

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Remembered my last experience here several years ago as an excellent meal. This time, was not as impressed. Although I very much enjoyed to antipasta dishes- stuffed pearl onions and a well-plated beet salad, my partner's entree pork chop was fatty and rare. And I was hoping to a flavorful pasta that could be a vegetarian entree but it seemed to need more seasoning. Still enjoyed the ambiance and service, but hoping next time I'll enjoy the dinner options more.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Everything was exceptional. The host could have had more of a personality but that‚Äôs just a personal opinion. The server was great - very friendly, helpful, and efficient. The food was all flavorful and well presented. If you‚Äôre visiting Seattle this restaurant is a must.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Small portions of food which did not taste good.  My hubs and I each had a cocktail, and they both tasted like mouth wash.  Dessert was delicious, and the service was excellent.  It had a nice atmosphere, but we were a little too close to our fellow diners.

Name: Spinasse
Comments: It was good. One of my favorite restaurant for date night.

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Exceptional!

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Year after year, meal after meal, Spinasse continues to demonstrate why they are in the top Italian restaurants in Seattle.   David brings his special touch to every dish leaving the kitchen.  A way wonderful neighborhood restaurant with global reach.   Every trip to Seattle must include a stop at this gem

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Great restaurant with great food, service, and wine list.  Angela, the wine manager is exceptional, and provided a great wine recommendation.

Name: Spinasse

Name: Spinasse
Comments: Very nice ambiance perfect for a date night. On the  overpriced side. The appetizers were much better than the actual meal (we got the sample of all 4 and it was excellent.) Name: Spinasse
Comments: The food is always so amazing and good, veggie and gluten free options too

Name: Spinasse
Comments: awesome,  great night for our anniversary.  will be coming back soon.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Food was amazing! At Francis is so lucky to have Chef Peter!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wine is always better with food and when accompanied with the delicious cuisine the chef has created makes for an amazing experience. Andrea and Renee are great hostesses and represent the brand very well.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We participate in St. Francis' food and wine pairing at least twice a year. This was our first visit this year with the new chef. The food was innovative, delicious and beautifully presented, and we look forward to more tastings from this chef. In the period of Covid, they have made adjustments to increase safety. There were only 10 people at the tasting (I think it usually was 18 or 20 in a room that holds 150+); our table was at least six feet from the nearest one, and we were near the doors which were open. All the wines were pre-poured and the food was delivered by masked staff wearing gloves. One issue: because the staff was all masked, it was difficult to hear/understand the staff explaining about the food and the wines; one staff in particular (new, I think?) was very hard to understand. But overall, a very enjoyable experience that felt quite safe.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Always a great experience.   Excellent food and wine!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The paired food and wine experience at St. Francis is fantastic.  The dishes presented were very delicious and unique.  Definitely things that I could/would never make at home.  One recommendation would be a palette cleanser between the final dish and dessert. Beautiful dining room.  Beautiful location.  Excellent service.  The host was informative and professional.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: I had a lovely experience! It started with walking onto the beautiful estate. I did the lunch tasting menu and the food was fantastic: perfectly seasoned, perfectly paired with the wines, perfectly portioned. It was an intimate experience as well. There were only 2 couples and I signed up on a Thursday morning. Our "guide" for the experience was knowledgeable, funny, and kind. And the chef came out to chat for a bit when we were all done. I'll definitely be checking out St. Francis again!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wonderful as always. The new chef is amazing!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Outstanding wine and food pairings. A great experience.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Delicious food and wine pairing. Always a special treat and always excellent.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Had missed the food and wine pairing during Covid stay at home orders. Went yesterday with smaller well placed grouping. With a new chef the menu was outstanding-the usual 5 course offering was plentiful and beautifully prepared and the wines continue to more than satisfy.Especially loved the scallop presentation and the duck.Can‚Äôt wait to return in the fall!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: I recommend this wine and food pairing experience to everyone.  Good food, good wine, great presentation and nice staff.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Great social distancing and safety with food handling and serving.  Highly recommended !

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Both the food and the wine were OIALEs.  (once in a lifetime experiences).   Proper safety quidelines were enforced without interfering with the beauty of the experience.  We enjoyed a beautiful view of Hood Mountain while we enjoyed some of the best food and wine of our lives.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We have been wine club members at St. Francis for many years and look forward to the annual complimentary food and wine pairing. The food is thoughtfully paired with wine ending the meal with port and a tasty dessert.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We do this every year for our anniversary and it never disappoints. Perfect pairing of  wines to moan-worthy dishes. Made even more notable this year as we were the last seating before the Corona Virus shutdown. Thank you to all the staff that made this special. Our hearts go out to you. We'll be back as soon as you reopen!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This wine and food pairing experience is a must if you are coming to wine country!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: If you are in Sonoma and able to get a reservation, do it! The food was incredible, the wine impeccable, the hosts were funny and knowledgeable. It was one of our favorite things we did during our visit. You won't regret it!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: One of the best lunches I have ever had. There were only 16 places at the two horseshoe tables, so intimate and participative. Wine and food pairings were spot on. We completely enjoyed it.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Best experience we had in Napa or Sonoma in combining wine and food.  Can't wait to go back again.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Even though the food was supposed to take a backseat to the wine, the food itself rivals that of many Michelin starred restaurants albeit without a lot of choices.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The wine and food pairing was fantastic.  Don‚Äôt miss if in the area but schedule in advance as it is very popular.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Outstanding in every way. Excellent food and very knowledgable staff. Makes learning about wine fun. Gorgeous setting. Our guests were so impressed on this their first visit that they joined the WineClub.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Fantastic food, wine and staff. I would highly recommend a visit.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Celebrating our Anniversary and had to make this one of our stops. Love it here. Food  and wine pairing is just perfect. So enjoy the small venue because you really get to know the other guest for the seating. Every time we come it‚Äôs special. Great value and delicious!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is always a new and exciting culinary and viticultural experience.  I highly recommend this experience to everyone, the team is amazing! The food is lovely and so filling! I only wish they were closer to my home, I'd go weekly as it's such a value.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Fabulous food paired with amazing wines, beautifully presented in a most entertaining and engaging way.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Third time and never disappointed.   Food pairings were perfect.  Hosts were helpful, perhaps a little more about the wine and a little less shtick. Could have taken a little more time.  All in all still the best experience in town.  Hope you take the suggestions as opportunities, not criticisms.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: We booked the wine and food pairing and it was the highlight of our trip to the Sonoma Valley. The food was amazing, the wine was amazing, and the staff made the event educational and fun without any wine snobbery. Can‚Äôt wait to go back!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Mother-Daughter trip

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is what a wine and food pairing should be!  More than just a bit of meat or a bit of cheese, these were chef creations that really allowed one to appreciate the wine being tasted.  On top of that Tamara and Andrea were superb hosts that really added to the experience.  We will assuredly do this again!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: This is a great way to enjoy St Francis' wine.  The food is amazing and service always enjoyable!  This was trip number 3 and I can't wait to go back again.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: FABULOUS ‚ù§Ô∏è

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Have been several times.  Never disappointed.  Jonna Schafer.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Our annual visit for delicious food and wine.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: The food and wine tasting at St. Francis Winery was amazing! I highly recommend it, everything was delicious and the service was exceptional.

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Wonderful wine and food pairing!  Every course was perfectly paired and quite delicious.  We highly recommend the St. Francis wine and food pairing.  They never disappoint!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Could not been nicer event to take a friend for her birthday.  Food, wine, hostesses could not have been better!  The winery is itself is intimate and inviting.  Only pleasant memories on all count!

Name: St. Francis Winery & Vineyards
Comments: Delicious food and wine with a fun atmosphere!

The box was given to one of the other guests at my table , fortunately they came back to my home for coffee and dessert and we were able to make the switch #2 when I opened my box to put the leftovers in a plastic container my crab imperial was NOT included with my leftovers and that really angered me because I purposely saved my crab to be enjoyed Sunday! And the extra that I paid for was waisted! I immediately called your restaurant but of course got voicemail and so  I left a message about my experience. Of course I did not hear back from anyone. Honestly, I didn‚Äôt expect to hear back ! I had heard so many good things about your establishment and was happy that we were able to FINALLY GET A TABLE! But my experience left me disappointed.Sincerely , Sandra Morlino

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay

The food and service, as always were outstanding.  The pace was relaxing and enjoyable.  The consistent excellence is the reason it has been our favorite restaurant for many years.

Name: Steve & Cookie's By the Bay
Comments: The theory of rural inflation is proven once again. This is a very good restaurant serving very good food but it can‚Äôt possibly be one of the best 100 restaurants in the United States. I have eaten in and reviewed fine restaurants around the world and there is no way that this falls into the top class. What keeps Steve and Cookies by the bay from being a five star restaurant? 1) Presentation. It is barely above the dreaded ‚Äúfood on a plate‚Äù category, it is far short of artful. 2) Attire of assistant waiters who all wear printed black tee shirts, fine at the shore but it is not the dress of a 5 star restaurant. 3) Blatant racism in work expectations. Waiters almost all seem to be white work at a good pace and take the time to be pleasant, assistants in black tee shirts work at a frenzied pace of a car wash as if expecting to be fired at any second. Almost all of the sub class appear to be Hispanic. This just isn‚Äôt seen anymore. Very good meals and very good service in a rather plain atmosphere, solid 4 star stuff.

Comments: My favorite restaurant!  Does not disappoint!  Excellent all around.

From there we went to dinner where we were escorted onto an enchanting patio with a view of the ocean. The service was amazing and our food was some of the best we have ever tasted. We had Brussel sprouts, a nice salad, halibut and filet mignon. We ended up with chocolate souffl√© and the homemade mint ice cream. Both were so yummy. We've been here many times and every single time is an amazing experience!  Wish we could post the entire course but definitely get any and all add-ons if you only plan on going here once!

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: As a huge Sushi Nakazawa fan, I was more than excited to take my brother to lunch at the sushi bar for his birthday. I was lucky to eat here last year and had an absolutely fantastic experience - which made me even more dissapointed in my most recent experience. My brother has celiac disease, which can be an issue at other restaurants, but Sushi Nakazawa reassured us that accommodating his dietary restrictions would not be an issue - we made sure to call ahead of time, remind the host, and checked with our waiter twice. But unfortunately, within an hour after eating, my brother was extremely sick. We had the same exact meal and I was completely fine. When you're paying the prices that you do at Sushi Nakazawa, and have been reassured that they can handle customers with celiac, it's quite frustrating when they fail to do so. The next day I called the restaurant to let them know what happened and the host kindly said they would have management follow-up, but 2 weeks have passed and I haven't heard anything - not even an apology. Shocking when you expect high quality customer service from a restaurant of this quality. This truly is an amazing sushi restaurant, but if you have dietary restrictions, eat at your own risk.

Name: Sushi Nakazawa - Sushi Bar
Comments: As close to Japan as you will find in New York.  Innovative touches on fabulous traditional sushi.

Our dinner experience was first and foremost time well spent together, made sweeter by the cozy ambiance, tasty omakase, delightful tea, and thoughtful service. We enjoyed watching the chefs at work and our exchanges with the staff were brief. If this is the kind of thing your after, go for it. Looking forward to our next meal at Sushi Nakazawa!

Thank you to the entire team and enjoy the night shift tonight!! Cheers!! Your good friend, George

Comments: Apps and dessert were very good.  Lots of extra 'goodies'.  Entree - both the scallops and the steak, were fairly mediocre for a place charging top-end.

Name: The Table at Season To Taste
Comments: The Table is a wonderful restaurant for special occasion dinners. The prix fixe menu rotates every six weeks and reflects an eclectic set of courses employing ingredients and techniques from around the world. There are two dishes offered for each of the four courses, so go with a loved one and taste every offering. I've gone twice so far and each of the eight dishes I've tried has been creative and excellent. The noise level is low enough to talk comfortably but the tables are separate enough to keep conversations private. You can tell that the staff team is tight knit and enjoys working together. They are supremely knowledgeable and engaged with each other and the patrons, and with little separation between the kitchen and the tables, you can see the food prepared with care. If you didn't like tripe or skate wing (and we didn't), you were out of luck.  However, the real problem was the truly horrible music and the volume at which it was played.  I like everything from Metallica to Bill Evans.  This was just loud noise with a heavy bass.  My guess is that it was there primarily for the chefs in the open kitchen, but it was blaring throughout the tiny dining room.  It was the kind of loud noise the CIA would use to extract a confession.  It ruined the experience completely.  The value proposition is poor at best at $150 a person with beer, no wine.  The chair are hard, no table cloths, and the decor was essentially nonexistent.  A few plastic flowers.  Overall, a huge disappointment.  Excellent bread and butter though.

Serving chicken as part of a fine dining menu is risky and this time it did not really paid off. My preference is that the restaurant stick to higher quality meats.  Also, I love bubbly wine with my meal and the only choice by the glass started at $17/glass.  I would like to find also quality sparkling wine choices in the $11-12/glass range too so I can have a couple without breaking the bank.  We will keep coming back always hope for a better experience.

It was fantastic, and the reputation of the restaurant is deserved. However, there was an intangible missing from the food that kept the meal from entering the upper echelon of meals I‚Äôve had. That said, I‚Äôll gladly return when there is a special occasion that calls for a meal to match.

As a couple we like to order one of everything on the menu and as each course arrives each have half of the 2 dishes. This means we get to taste everything - and believe me, you don't want to miss anything. The food is different every time we go and the wines are always interesting. The waitstaff can tell you the details of each one and why it goes with the particular dish. It's not overbearing wine-speak it's genuinely interesting information. It is not inexpensive - but it is worth every cent. You leave with a complimentary, home-made granola bar in your pocket feeling replete and well cared for.

We were in the most lit area (right next to the light wall) and we had trouble seeing. Just to exit the restaurant my one friend had to use a flashlight. It‚Äôs definitely not disability friendly at all. The staff was nice, the food was great. Overall it was a lovely beautiful night, and the food was very satisfying. We ordered the beef short ribs (4.5 ‚≠êÔ∏è), scallops (3.5 ‚≠êÔ∏è) and beets (4 ‚≠êÔ∏è). I‚Äôll say the one uncomfortable moment was when waiting for the check to sign, I noticed a manager or higher up kept staring us down as if we were over staying out welcome. This kept on after we signed. It was a party of 4 at 9:30 at night, and we had barely stayed 65 minutes at that point with a 8:15p reservation. It was extremely uncomfortable, and honestly made me wonder if it was racial possibly with us being probably the only or one of the only tables of POC. Hopefully not related but who knows.

Name: Townsend

Name: Townsend
Comments: This may be a great spot-  but only after they fix some startup problems.Our table was not ready at our reservation time but there is under zero space to wait - except at the overcrowded bar (with others waiting to be seated) so we hung out in a window area. We had a wonderful server who took our order for a nice bottle of wine (from a moderately interesting list). A runner then brought us the obligatory bread basket along with an amuse-bouche of vinegared beets, one of which he  overturned onto the table linens - but made no offer to even cover the large and expanding beet red amoeba shaped stain with a napkin.Our first courses - a nice potato potage and baked oysters with (I recall) Pernod were quite well prepared. Our mains, a duck breast and a fish with a leek and other vegetable pur√©e were both well prepared - but suffered from an obvious many too many minutes late delay in getting from the kitchen to the table. We passed on desert as nothing on the limited selection spoke to us.This is a work in progress. Most of the ‚Äúrough edges‚Äù we felt were managed around by a wonderful and obviously experienced server (who we well tipped) but it‚Äôs hard to not get the feeling that the front and back of the house need some more time working together.Last - it‚Äôs a fine dining restaurant.  It needs some acoustic treatment as the noise level was close to that of a sports bar until later in the evening when the number of patrons was at a minimum.We will give it a few months and return.

Name: Townsend
Comments: First time at the new location (but several times at the old)- so my advice now is - ask for a table against the wall or upstairs.  The window tables are very cold in winter and the one nearest to the service station is distracting. The food - well, I just don't get the hype!  It's good but not spectacular in any form.  Sweetbreads were overly large and thus contained significant cartilage.  Tuna nicoise was grainy... in general the entire meal was overly salted.  Maybe I'm being picky but for a top place it was disappointing and all this was reflected in prior visits.

Name: Townsend
Comments: Seating was swift when we arrived with our reservation (which we made 15 mins prior); the food was all fantastic - from the amuse-bouche to the sophisticated dessert. Everything was so fresh and extremely well executed. It's a masterclass in French cuisine.

Comments: I have never left a poor review. We were really looking forward to trying Townsend as we have heard great things. However, the food was extremely mediocre - some lukewarm, some so hot as if out of a microwave. It lacked any real flavor. The foie gras mousse was gummy like glue and the duck was questionably duck. The only thing actually worth eating were the oysters. Our meal was so disappointing we immediately walked to Friday, Saturday, Sunday where we know we can get a top-notch, perfectly executed meal with staff that don‚Äôt seem like robots. Just having a reputation for good food won‚Äôt do much unless you only serve people who would be happy eating at Applebee‚Äôs every night. We won‚Äôt be returning.

We did and the GM, Brian, made sure to stop by during our most recent visit. Our experience was great and Brian made sure to take care of our party. It's very refreshing to see an organization do everything they could to turn around a less than stellar experience. Mistakes and off days certainly happen, so we appreciate when a group can recover and make sure to create a good experience going forward. Food was great and service was great also including for our young son.

It was in a great location and the restaurant itself is spacious and beautiful - not typical for many restaurants in the city.  Food was very good - we went with the server's recommendations and were not disappointed.  My husband had the fried chicken sandwich and I had the Egg and Tortilla.  I asked for scrambled eggs instead of fried egg and it was no problem.  We had mimosas and Bloody Marys and then finished with the Donuts. We wouldn't normally do that but the donuts were recommended.  Enjoyed the experience from start to finish - we will definitely be back.

Name: Upland
Comments: Loved everything about it. Food service and decor were all absolutely perfect.

Name: Upland
Comments: I went early with a friend.  We ordered a few appetizers and some wine.  Nice sized portions and very fresh food.  Excellent service.  Will definitely come back

Name: Upland
Comments: I have been coming to Upland since it first opened and it has been a consistently good experience in terms of both food and service.  Unfortunately on my last visit our server was SO RUDE and put us on edge for the entire dinner because we were nervous of being barked at!  She tried to take our appetisers away when we were half way though and when we said we weren‚Äôt finished yet, she decided she would change our plates for some unknown reason...then a minute later our mains arrived so we ended up not actually being able to enjoy the rest of our appetisers!  It was quite embarrassing because I had a guest in from out of town and got them to cancel their reservation at L‚ÄôArtusi to come to Upland instead!  I really hope it was a one off be side I really do enjoy Upland, but next time I will think twice before returning since New York is full of great restaurants with great service.

Name: Upland
Comments: Expensive. Noisy.  Pizza was burnt.  My friend asked for a slight modification in her meal (a vegetable instead of the rice) and the waiter didn't even try to accommodate.  Highly overrated.

Name: Upland
Comments: The service was truly terribly. Our server was very stuck up and almost acted like it was a burden to serve us. The food was also overly salty. My favourite thing was the caesar salad.

Name: Upland
Comments: Our server was grumpy and I was surprised because I have usually had really lovely service.   It kind of bummed me out.  I loved our meal despite him but it bothered me a lot, I have been in food service and I know when someone is over it, it shows.   Otherwise Jennifer made it right by coming over to check on us!

Name: Upland
Comments: We agreed that this is our favorite NYC restaurant, hands-down.  Impeccable food and service, both enjoyed in a beautiful and quiet room. We will keep returning.

Name: Upland
Comments: Wonderful brunch, great drinks and very professional staff.

Name: Upland
Comments: We went to Upland for a celebratory engagement dinner with both sets of parents.  This place is incredible.  Every dish is well thought out and you don't need to spend an arm & a leg for a truly great meal like other places in NYC.  Highly recommend the hen of the wood, tomato soup & caesar salad

Name: Upland
Comments: Such a fantastic meal with fantastic service!!

Name: Upland
Comments: Great vibe and great food. Loved that you could have a conversation

Name: Upland
Comments: This is usually a fave but was quite disappointing.  Our waitress tried to rush us and my main dish (salmon) had strange sides.

Name: Upland
Comments: Pizzas and salads are great.  I had the feta spinach omelet, but it did not have much feta or spinach in it.  The slice of bread given the side was truly hard as a rock, so could not break or bite.  Otherwise it is a great place.  Service, ambiance and staff are great.  Will skip the omlette next time.

Name: Upland
Comments: I love this restaurant. The atmosphere is clean and crisp and appeases anyone's taste/style. The wait staff was incredibly kind and my server was specifically awesome. I took two friends and I would highly suggest this as a restaurant to take someone who is in town for the weekend. We shared an order of donuts at the beginning and the jelly donut was the best I have ever had - huge shout-out to the pastry chef :) All three of our meals were pretty stellar - my one and only hesitation is that it can get quite costly but with that being said, the portions are quite large and we all three had food to-go for later. Thank you!!!

Name: Upland
Comments: Such a treat. The food is inventive and great. And a fun vibe.

Name: Upland
Comments: Food and service were great. Two outstanding pastas. Beautiful space with a great vibe. Great meal always consistent

Name: Upland
Comments: Would never go back because of noise level tho good excellent

Name: Upland
Comments: The food is unique and delicious... the cocktail drink menu was very good!

Name: Upland
Comments: There's a reason Upland is always one of my favorite restaurants in the city - they always deliver great food and experience

Name: Upland
Comments: We had a great evening here. Great food and service , and a really lively buzzy ambience. All you want from a restaurant !

Name: Upland
Comments: Great food! Great location! Energetic noise level!

Name: Upland
Comments: We went for a casual meal. The service was great. I spilt my espresso martini and they made me a new one straight away

Name: Upland
Comments: Great dining experience! Will visit again!

Name: Upland
Comments: Great food! Love the decor!

Name: Upland
Comments: Staff was great but the burger was terrible.

Name: Upland
Comments: This was my second time here and both times, I really enjoyed it. I came for my birthday brunch and we were a party of 4. The first table we were seated at wasn't great, but they let us have a booth and it was much better. The hostesses were very kind and accommodating. Service was good - I always had water in my glass. The atmosphere is so lovely and comfortable! The food was excellent. The sausage and kale pizza is phenomenal. Usually I don't like thicker pizzas but this one managed to be thick without being too heavy or soggy. The crust was crispy and the flavor was out of this world. We also enjoyed the burger very much. The fried chicken sandwich was a bit on the small side but very tasty. Overall, great experience and would go back.

Name: Upland
Comments: Enjoyed brunch at Upland this last weekend! Food and service was fantastic!

Name: Upland
Comments: Always the best!

Name: Upland
Comments: We had a great dinner --our usual favorites: the 'nduja pizza, the skirt steak, the little gem salad ... all fantastic.  Also an amazing wine list. Fabulous.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: What a gem of a restaurant!  Truly a fabulous meal.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: I love this place, if it weren't so difficult to get a reservation, I'd go more often.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Food is amazing - difficult to get a reservation or seat at the bar.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of the few restaurants that actually gets better with age.  Each service person, from the water boy to the manager, glides around attentively to serve patrons.  The wine list is small but select.  pours are very large.  I loved my duck breast, which is always served medium rare (perfect).  Staff is very attentive, with one staff dedicated to just polishing wine glasses.  All details combine to make this a 5 star restaurant.  Others agree, which is why at 5:15 pm on Thursday it was jammed with couples.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Great local spot, excellent cocktails, vibrant energy and location.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This was my second visit here and everything was great! I am adding to my list of favorite Philly restaurants. My favorite thing I ordered was the crispy artichokes.  Delicious!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: 25th anniversary I the food was delicious

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Vernick never disappoints!  Everything from the appetizers, to entrees, to wine was outstanding.  One my favorite restaurants in Philadelphia!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: As always, dining at Vernick is a wonderful experience. Very good food, drinks and pleasant ambiance. Looking forward to returning for another dinner

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Loved sitting at the Chefs counter. Awesome experience!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was delicious! The foie gras was probably our favorite of all the small plates we got. The menu was excellent it was hard to make choices because we wanted everything! The cocktails were really good too; strong and refreshing. Can‚Äôt wait to go back!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Vernick was incredible. Service was outstanding! We had a variety of dishes and were not disappointed by any of them, and some were down right amazing. Definitely worth the wait for a reservation.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Outstanding original menu creations each with their own x-factor. The white truffle tagliatelle special is indeed very special.  Well thought out wine selections by glass or bottle compliment the plates.  Servus is first rate - attentive, comprehensive, but not overbearing.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was incredible food and service Can‚Äôt wait to go back

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: fantastic service, food, and drinks.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Was just okay. Don‚Äôt get all the hype.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Amazing experience. Well worth the wait!  Outstanding execution. Terrific service.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of the best Restaurants in Philadelphia and absolutely wonderful fare.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Britten was exceptional again.. everything was spectacular top to bottom

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: We just locked the food. If you have mobility issues ask to sit downstairs

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: The pumpkin toast, roasted cabbage, and curry shrimp were spectacular. The ravioli was good but it was weird that it was just one giant one, also for the price it wasn‚Äôt much. The mushroom toast was good but I think it would have been more enjoyable if it was warm and not served cold. My friend enjoyed the oysters. The service was great! I went to dinner with a friend I haven‚Äôt seen in a year and is in town for Thanksgiving and it was nice that they recommended that we take our time ordering and that there would be 15-20 min between each plate, so we could really enjoy our chatting over the sparkling wine (which I never heard about until dinner tonight!). Definitely will return to Vernick with my husband as I think he‚Äôd enjoy it.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Outstanding restaurant from the moment we walked in until we left. The staff was exceptional, our server was on point, and the food was even better than I could have hoped for: inventive, exciting, and most importantly, delicious! Well done!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This is the best restaurant in Philly. The most creative and fresh ideas i've seen. I'm a vegetarian, and there are many options!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Anniversary

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Service was amazing. Food was delicious although I felt a few of the dishes were on the salty side (the mushroom soup amuse bouche, sea urchin with scrambled eggs, gratin that came with the sea bass)

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Dinner was excellent, as always!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Loved everything!!! Omg the best!!Can‚Äôt wait to go back.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One of our favorite restaurants anywhere! We dine here whenever we come to Philadelphia (we live in NYC) and have even talked about hopping on the train just to dine here!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: The food was very good admittedly a bit pricey for what it was. I did find the food was extremely rich.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Gorgeous menu, beautiful presentation, great wait staff, noisy but worth it!  We‚Äôll go again!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Fantastic service and incredible food. I can‚Äôt wait to go back!

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Unbelievable experience, food was exceptional and service was too. I've been trying to get in here on previous trips to Philly and it did not disappoint. One of the better meal experiences ive had in awhile

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: This is an AMAZING restaurant.  If you consider yourself a foodie then you MUST go here.  Everything we ordered and everything that was complementary was absolutely delicious and wonderful.  I wanted to keep eating and ordering dish after dish.  I went to philly for a few days and was doing research to find the best place to dine and Vernick is the place!  I live in NJ and eat in NYC all the time and I would definitely go back to Philly just to eat at Vernick (I revisited yesterday and it was delicious). I ate at the chef counter a second time and would recommend eating there just to see the chefs work like a well oiled machine with everyone moving with precision and dedicated passion.I went a second time and this place is AMAZING.  The chefs are rock stars and had another amazing enjoyable dinner.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Awesome all around experience! My wife and I are huge foodies and haven‚Äôt been so satisfied since dining at California Grill, Victoria and Alberts, and Flying Fish. Everything was spot on and perfect. Thank you for a wonderful experience.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: First time visit - enjoyed ourselves very much. Highly recommend.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Excellent service and wonderful tastes! Entrees lacked the luster that I had hoped to continue after our toasts and small plates.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: One would be hard pressed to find a more delicious meal, it was superb! There is always room for improvement so if I could improve anything... well... the service could be a tad warmer.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Been here many times amd have never been disappointed.   Looking forward to our next visit.

Name: Vernick Food & Drink
Comments: Everything was fantastic. The service,the food and the atmosphere.A true  5 star experience

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Everything about Vetri was wonderful. From the service to the granola goody bag‚Äîwe couldn‚Äôt have celebrated a 21st birthday any better.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I was there to celebrate my son and his wife having gotten him through graduation with a Doctorate in Physical Therapy from Arcadia University.  We were all very much impressed with Vetri Cucina.  The food was outstanding (and ample), the service was impeccable, and it was an altogether outstanding experience.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: An amazing evening from start to finish. The staff were so warm and welcoming. The meal was a modified prefix menu. By modified,  I mean that specific foods of interest were included while foods noted to be of lesser interest were not included. The beginning was with a creatively tasty aperitivo, served with fois gras pastrami on a slice of brioche, high temperature baked and charred cauliflower, smoked duck breast and crudities with a balsamic mayonnaise. Then the serious food started.... hamachi crudo with a creative use of citrus to give it sparkle, onion crepe, with perfectly caramelized onion that took 2 days to make. We tried six different pastas, all delicious; however, for me the ricotta ravioli were incredible.... light as a feather, creamy, and, again, set off with a creative use of citrus In keeping with the season. The real showstopper were three perfectly cooked and sauced Nantucket scallops, topped with a generous serving of ostera caviar and tiny house-made potato chips. So good I felt we should eat this dish on our knees. Entrees hadn't even been started at this point. Spit-roasted goat... tender, juicy with crunchy skin and a salt-baked bronzino were secondi. Desserts were equally amazing. We ended up eating on and taking the others home for the next day. Bravo to Vetri Cucina!!!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Seriously delicious eclectic cuisine... we shared many unique courses and wine pairings that we loved! If you love food and unique experiences this is the place

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I had high expectations for my birthday dinner. I was so not disappointed. From the moment we arrived we were greeted and felt welcome. The food, oh it was sooo very good. I got to try things like froe gras and white truffles. I have eaten at many fine restaurants, but this has to be number one. Yes it is very expensive, the most expensive of any restaurant I have ever visited... but oh so very worth the experience.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Vetri never disappoints!  And their Friday lunch is a treat and a bargain!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Once again, a memorable dining experience.Some of the best dishes I have ever had.Grazie

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: From start, and I mean very start with a personal phone call right after I booked thanking me for my reservation, and throughout the evening, every aspect of the dinner was superb, without any air of snootiness one comes to experiences 5 star restaurants. Very special, yet comfortable and accommodating.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Great service and excellent job with wine pairings. Food was not great. Sauces were all very similar (brown butter based). Also, concept of wait staff picking our menu choices sounds fun in concept, but my wife and I agreed that our experience would have been better had we got to pick our own food. Glad we had the experience, but wouldn‚Äôt hurry back anytime soon

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Always great! We love bill!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I'm not sure which was better: the food or the service.  The entirety of the meal was the best I can remember.  Being greater with a drink and snacks.  Amazing service and presentation.  And the quality and execution of the meals was second to none.  Hope to be back soon.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Best lunch experience - always.  Worth taking a Friday off.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: From start to finish our evening at Vetri was exceptional. Of course the food was delicious and beautifully plated but our wait staff made the experience that much nicer. They were attentive without being intrusive and we were impressed by the knowledge of our dietary restrictions. All agreed that this was our best meal in Philadelphia.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: The best dining experience in the city.  Unique flavors, perfect service.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: When people hear about the cost of my meal, they cringe and obviously do not understand "value". When a product or experience is extraordinary, then there is no concern about cost and that makes a great value. This was a dining experience without compare. The food was fantastic from start to finish, and the wine was a perfect compliment. The service was fabulous and the servers absolutely helped to make the experience special. It was my 25th wedding anniversary and my wife and I shared it with my 3 daughters.  I hit a grand slam with my choice of Vetri Cucina! Thank you all for making it a very memorable, lovely and satisfying evening!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Best food in the city, state and maybe northeast!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: This restaurant was a great experience for foodies looking for a fancy night out. It is a great way to try new things and the homemade pasta was perfect!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Excellent experience. Outstanding, detailed, creative, delicious food with an Italian focus.  It also is a home-y unpretentious setting which is perfect. The desserts were the best we've ever tasted. Would consider again for a very special occasion.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Delicious meal, service so over the top that it was a bit much or uncomfortable at times, felt a little robotic/insincere, but it is a very formal place. Great experience, something to try once and the food was phenomenal. Price tag a bit extreme. For dinner for two and bottle of wine on the less expensive side of their offerings, bill was $440 not including tip. When comparing to the nicer, expensive places like some of the Steven starr and steakhouses in the city, it‚Äôs more expensive.. but again, an experience! And despite the tasting sizes, they sprinkle in lots of extras and you leave stuffed!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: The most fantastic food in Philly, but if you do the tasting menu, be prepared to consume a LOT of food! So unexpected, we are big eaters and have never been beaten by a meal! We surrendered before the last savory course, and before cheeses and dessert....these were not large portions, but there were many courses. I suggest getting up and having a brief walk outside at the 5th or 6th course! If you can afford an expensive meal, this is worth it.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: once again, this is my favorite restaurant in the world! the food is so good you can't believe it. everything about this place is top notch. of course you pay for it but why not live a little. I highly recommend this for any occation.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Food was amazing. Waiter let us try wine by the glass before selecting. Plus his service and attention were top notch. Each course both of us got a different selection chosen by the chef which let us try a majority if the dishes. Cannot wait to go back.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Superb in every way!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: How was my meal?  What more can I say then the BEST Italian restaurant in the entire Phila area. Including ACNJ.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My friend and I enjoyed our lunch.The food was great, service attentive.- - but still rather pricey.The place could use a good cleaning.  But , overall, a lovely meal with happy (holiday) vibe.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Vetri Cucina delivers perfection in dining. Atmosphere, food and service just perfect. The decor is casual elegance. The service is highly professional never affected. The staff are attentive without being over bearing. The sense is they want you to have a wonderful dining experience. The food is inventive but never pretentious. Flavor reigns via superb ingredients in well conceived dishes. This is truly a world class restaurant.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My wife and I dined here as part of an anniversary celebration. The restaurant is warm and quiet-a great place to have conversation and enjoy the meal. We were served a lovely cocktail-an Italian spritz-while the staff asked us about likes, dislikes, allergies, etc. We were given the option of choosing from their tasting menu or to be surprised. We opted for the surprise-but did not do the optional wine pairing (too much alcohol for a couple of light-weights!). My wife has very distinct food dislikes and I am very adventurous and chef was marvelous at meeting both our preferences! The portions were small and manageable, the food was gorgeous and delicious. The service was gracious, friendly and attentive but not cloying. Definitely worth going for a special occasion!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Great special occasion but will tip a hole in the wallet!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Amazing! I've never been so full but I just couldn't stop eating. Expensive, but well worth it.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Love Love Love! Best Birthday Dinner ever. Thank for the amazing food, wine, and above all care to everything!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Bill, our waiter, was fantastic!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: One of the best meals I‚Äôve had! If you‚Äôre in Philly, definitely eat here.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Superb attention to detail by The Culinary staff and front-of-the-house staff was marvelously accommodating.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: One of the best dining experiences you'll have.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Always an outstanding culinary and service experience with a mix of old favorites, new dishes and wonderful wine pairings!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: I have eaten recently recently at L'ambroisie, Le clarence, garance, Tour d'Argent, Restaurant du Palais Royal, Le Gabriel, Gabriel Kreuther. vetri is an old favorite of mine. I have eaten here 10 times. The food was mixed. Within the tasting menu format, 3 or 4 dishes were brilliant. A few very ordinary.The service was also very mixed. Our main server was really good, but the others were poor. Compared to lunch at "Restaurant du Palais Royal", vetri was inferior, and poor value.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: An incredible meal! The food and wine pairing was SO good! The service was phenomenal as well. And it was really cool that Mark Vetri took the time to make the rounds and spend a couple minutes talking to us. Fantastic overall meal, a must if you are in the area! Cheers!!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Very good, not great.  This is due to the temperature of the pastas and the main courses.  Without exception, every dish came to the table lukewarm, like they were sitting around in the kitchen and not made to order.  For the price, I would have expected better.

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: My favorite part of this whole experience was constructing the tasting menu. Our server, Tara, came to our table and announced we were to have a discussion regarding what we enjoy eating and what we do not. Was there anything we felt we absolutely needed to try? Any ingredients of which we are particularly fond? I wish every restaurant with an unset tasting menu did this, it's brilliant. Ultimately, we did not choose any particular courses, so it was a surprise, but a surprise built around our tastes. There were six main courses, 3 bread courses, an amuse-bouche, and a couple mignardises. Every other main course had an additional entree we shared. Our tasting menus were completely different from one another, so we were able to try each other's entrees as well. Overall, we tried a little over 20 dishes. All of them were exquisite and definitely on the richer side. I was pretty full about two-thirds of the way through.What made the experience amazing, food aside, was our brilliant server. Tara is an absolute food genius, emotionally intelligent, and easy to understand. Her knowledge is vast and gave an immediate answers to every question without missing a single beat. Playful and understanding, she intuitively knew when to give us space as well as when to swoop in with another brilliant display. Truly a magical night and reunion with my father, made special by Tara. P.S. I'm sorry for tripping you, I still feel guilty!

Name: Vetri Cucina
Comments: Excellent culinary experience. Superb staff and support.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: My favorite boston restaurant.  Great atmosphere, food, service, and value.  Highly recommend.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Yvonne‚Äôs is my new favorite Boston restaurant. The space is unique and comfortable but with a wow factor. The small plates menu is very well balanced with meat, cheese, vegan options. Our party of four ordered 10 plates and each was uniquely seasoned, spectacular in taste and presentation. ‚ÄúHolly‚Äù our waitress was a fount of knowledge about the menu but also Locke Ober, the men‚Äôs club previously in the space for a very long time. We all enjoyed learning about the interiors and renovations. Don‚Äôt change a thing!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Jessica needs to time down her attitude. Awful customer service.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We have been wanting to go to Yvonne‚Äôs for a while and it just never seems to happen.   I have to say it was worth the wait. The menu has lots of short plates and we had many.  Every single item we had was delicious.  Don‚Äôt miss the fritters!   Just an incredible experience.  Our server wasn‚Äôt the best but she has lots of other staff helping and they were all great.  For the ‚Äúfeast‚Äù we had the brisket which was totally worth the wait.   Can‚Äôt wait to go back and try the few dishes we didn‚Äôt eat.  Can‚Äôt say enough great things about this place

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Special place, amazing ambience, incredible bar, delicious food

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: There is no better place to have a special holiday dinner.... this has become a tradition for four of us ... the food is spectacular  in taste and presentation and everyone from entering the restaurant to wait staff is super nice.... unpretentious and great people... thank you !

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: One bartender let my wife sit there for 7-8 mins without asking her if she wanted anything... Paige the other bartender was good and we‚Äôre glad she was there. Our service at the table was very good, would just avoid that one bartender (sorry, didn‚Äôt get a name)

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We're big fans of Yvonne's, and while we don't go as often as we'd like, when we go our experience is excellent.We went because it was our anniversary, and our server helped make it even more special.  He recommended drinks and other menu items, took pictures for us, let my wife try a drink to be sure it was what she expected.  Great service!Our reservation was early, so it wasn't super busy, and relatively quiet.  Seemed like a good time to go if you wanted a reasonable noice level.  Dinner on a Thursday - Saturday can be quite noisy.For new visitors, think of it as mostly small plates for sharing.  Well seasoned, good quality.  We loved the lamb, the beef tartar, and potato snacks (the menu name escapes me).  The desserts didn't measure up to the rest of the menu, and were just ok.We spent about $100pp and felt like it was good value for a special occasion.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: I came here with my boyfriend for our anniversary dinner. Yvonne‚Äôs really went above and beyond! I had indicated that it was our anniversary on opentable and take gave us some complimentary champagne to start off the night. The food and drinks were amazing and the service was great as well!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Very romantic. The food was superb and the service was excellent. Prices were good as well.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: I have only been to Yvonne's once and I tried to return just a week later but they were already booked! The food has a lot of flavors and came out as it was ready -- I highly recommend the hummus and shrimp!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Really cool vibe and great food.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Definitely recommended for cocktails, but could get better food for the same price elsewhere.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We were really enjoying our evening at the bar, the drinks were great and the ambiance was perfect. But once we were brought to our dinner table the night changed. Our host escorted us past several open tables in the main dining area through a clandestine passageway into a completely different part of the Yvonne's that I was not expecting. Although intrigued at first by the completely different decor, the dark space and thumping techno music just wasn't for me. It was too loud and too club-like for what we had in mind. Given how different the two sections are, I wish the host, the website or someone gave us a choice of seating space in advance. The food was great. Not rushing to go back.

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: We have been making Yvonne's a tradition to begin our evening's prior to the opening night at the Boston Ballet and have to say that the menu changes are wonderful - always great to change things up! The food is, as always, creative and delicious! The cocktails are fabulous and the wine list is excellent! We love Yvonne's and look forward to our next evening there!!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Such a great place, dishes were delicious and well thought out. Hit all the right taste buds and drinks were top notch!Recommend the steak tartare toast, lamb ribs, tater tot squares.Josephine baker was a delicious drink to end the meal!

Name: Yvonne's
Comments: Awesome spot for a Friday night! Our server was the best, had great recommendations for both food and drinks. Will definitely be going back soon!

Name: Yvonne's
